377 NavEKF::NavEKF(const AP_AHRS *ahrs, AP_Baro &baro, const RangeFinder &rng) :
378  _ahrs(ahrs),
379  _baro(baro),
380  _rng(rng),
381  state(*reinterpret_cast<struct state_elements *>(&states)),
382  gpsNEVelVarAccScale(0.05f), // Scale factor applied to horizontal velocity measurement variance due to manoeuvre acceleration - used when GPS doesn't report speed error
383  gpsDVelVarAccScale(0.07f), // Scale factor applied to vertical velocity measurement variance due to manoeuvre acceleration - used when GPS doesn't report speed error
384  gpsPosVarAccScale(0.05f), // Scale factor applied to horizontal position measurement variance due to manoeuvre acceleration
385  msecHgtDelay(60), // Height measurement delay (msec)
386  msecMagDelay(40), // Magnetometer measurement delay (msec)
387  msecTasDelay(240), // Airspeed measurement delay (msec)
388  gpsRetryTimeUseTAS(10000), // GPS retry time with airspeed measurements (msec)
389  gpsRetryTimeNoTAS(7000), // GPS retry time without airspeed measurements (msec)
390  gpsFailTimeWithFlow(5000), // If we have no GPS for longer than this and we have optical flow, then we will switch across to using optical flow (msec)
391  hgtRetryTimeMode0(10000), // Height retry time with vertical velocity measurement (msec)
392  hgtRetryTimeMode12(5000), // Height retry time without vertical velocity measurement (msec)
393  tasRetryTime(5000), // True airspeed timeout and retry interval (msec)
394  magFailTimeLimit_ms(10000), // number of msec before a magnetometer failing innovation consistency checks is declared failed (msec)
395  magVarRateScale(0.05f), // scale factor applied to magnetometer variance due to angular rate
396  gyroBiasNoiseScaler(2.0f), // scale factor applied to imu gyro bias learning before the vehicle is armed
397  accelBiasNoiseScaler(1.0f), // scale factor applied to imu accel bias learning before the vehicle is armed
398  msecGpsAvg(200), // average number of msec between GPS measurements
399  msecHgtAvg(100), // average number of msec between height measurements
400  msecMagAvg(100), // average number of msec between magnetometer measurements
401  msecBetaAvg(100), // average number of msec between synthetic sideslip measurements
402  msecBetaMax(200), // maximum number of msec between synthetic sideslip measurements
403  msecFlowAvg(100), // average number of msec between optical flow measurements
404  dtVelPos(0.2f), // number of seconds between position and velocity corrections. This should be a multiple of the imu update interval.
405  covTimeStepMax(0.07f), // maximum time (sec) between covariance prediction updates
406  covDelAngMax(0.05f), // maximum delta angle between covariance prediction updates
407  TASmsecMax(200), // maximum allowed interval between airspeed measurement updates
408  DCM33FlowMin(0.71f), // If Tbn(3,3) is less than this number, optical flow measurements will not be fused as tilt is too high.
409  fScaleFactorPnoise(1e-10f), // Process noise added to focal length scale factor state variance at each time step
410  flowTimeDeltaAvg_ms(100), // average interval between optical flow measurements (msec)
411  flowIntervalMax_ms(100), // maximum allowable time between flow fusion events
412  gndEffectTimeout_ms(1000), // time in msec that baro ground effect compensation will timeout after initiation
413  gndEffectBaroScaler(4.0f) // scaler applied to the barometer observation variance when operating in ground effect
414

428 // Check basic filter health metrics and return a consolidated health status
429 bool NavEKF::healthy(void) const
430 {
431  uint8_t faultInt;
432  getFilterFaults(faultInt);
433  if (faultInt > 0) {
434  return false;
435  }
436  if (_fallback && velTestRatio > 1 && posTestRatio > 1 && hgtTestRatio > 1) {
437  // all three metrics being above 1 means the filter is
438  // extremely unhealthy.
439  return false;
440  }
441  // Give the filter a second to settle before use
442  if ((imuSampleTime_ms - ekfStartTime_ms) < 1000 ) {
443  return false;
444  }
445  // barometer and position innovations must be within limits when on-ground
446  float horizErrSq = sq(innovVelPos[3]) + sq(innovVelPos[4]);
447  if (!vehicleArmed && (fabsf(innovVelPos[5]) > 1.0f || horizErrSq > 1.0f)) {
448  return false;
449  }
450 
451  // all OK
452  return true;
453 }
454 
455 // resets position states to last GPS measurement or to zero if in constant position mode
456 void NavEKF::ResetPosition(void)
457 {
458  if (constPosMode || (PV_AidingMode != AID_ABSOLUTE)) {
459  state.position.x = 0;
460  state.position.y = 0;
461  } else if (!gpsNotAvailable) {
462  // write to state vector and compensate for GPS latency
463  state.position.x = gpsPosNE.x + gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.x + 0.001f*velNED.x*float(_msecPosDelay);
464  state.position.y = gpsPosNE.y + gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.y + 0.001f*velNED.y*float(_msecPosDelay);
465  // the estimated states at the last GPS measurement are set equal to the GPS measurement to prevent transients on the first fusion
466  statesAtPosTime.position.x = gpsPosNE.x;
467  statesAtPosTime.position.y = gpsPosNE.y;
468  }
469  // stored horizontal position states to prevent subsequent GPS measurements from being rejected
470  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++){
471  storedStates[i].position.x = state.position.x;
472  storedStates[i].position.y = state.position.y;
473  }
474 }
475 
476 // Reset velocity states to last GPS measurement if available or to zero if in constant position mode or if PV aiding is not absolute
477 // Do not reset vertical velocity using GPS as there is baro alt available to constrain drift
478 void NavEKF::ResetVelocity(void)
479 {
480  if (constPosMode || PV_AidingMode != AID_ABSOLUTE) {
481  state.velocity.zero();
482  state.vel1.zero();
483  state.vel2.zero();
484  } else if (!gpsNotAvailable) {
485  // reset horizontal velocity states, applying an offset to the GPS velocity to prevent the GPS position being rejected when the GPS position offset is being decayed to zero.
486  state.velocity.x = velNED.x + gpsVelGlitchOffset.x; // north velocity from blended accel data
487  state.velocity.y = velNED.y + gpsVelGlitchOffset.y; // east velocity from blended accel data
488  state.vel1.x = velNED.x + gpsVelGlitchOffset.x; // north velocity from IMU1 accel data
489  state.vel1.y = velNED.y + gpsVelGlitchOffset.y; // east velocity from IMU1 accel data
490  state.vel2.x = velNED.x + gpsVelGlitchOffset.x; // north velocity from IMU2 accel data
491  state.vel2.y = velNED.y + gpsVelGlitchOffset.y; // east velocity from IMU2 accel data
492  // over write stored horizontal velocity states to prevent subsequent GPS measurements from being rejected
493  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++){
494  storedStates[i].velocity.x = velNED.x + gpsVelGlitchOffset.x;
495  storedStates[i].velocity.y = velNED.y + gpsVelGlitchOffset.y;
496  }
497  }
498 }
499 
500 // reset the vertical position state using the last height measurement
501 void NavEKF::ResetHeight(void)
502 {
503  // read the altimeter
504  readHgtData();
505  // write to the state vector
506  state.position.z = -hgtMea; // down position from blended accel data
507  state.posD1 = -hgtMea; // down position from IMU1 accel data
508  state.posD2 = -hgtMea; // down position from IMU2 accel data
509  // reset stored vertical position states to prevent subsequent GPS measurements from being rejected
510  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++){
511  storedStates[i].position.z = -hgtMea;
512  }
513  terrainState = state.position.z + rngOnGnd;
514 }
515 
516 // this function is used to initialise the filter whilst moving, using the AHRS DCM solution
517 // it should NOT be used to re-initialise after a timeout as DCM will also be corrupted
518 bool NavEKF::InitialiseFilterDynamic(void)
519 {
520  // this forces healthy() to be false so that when we ask for ahrs
521  // attitude we get the DCM attitude regardless of the state of AHRS_EKF_USE
522  statesInitialised = false;
523 
524  // If we are a plane and don't have GPS lock then don't initialise
525  if (assume_zero_sideslip() && _ahrs->get_gps().status() < AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D) {
526  return false;
527  }
528 
529  // If the DCM solution has not converged, then don't initialise,
530  // unless at least 30s has passed
531  if (_ahrs->get_error_rp() > 0.05f && _ahrs->uptime_ms() < 30000U) {
532  return false;
533  }
534 
535  // Set re-used variables to zero
536  InitialiseVariables();
537 
538  // get initial time deltat between IMU measurements (sec)
539  dtIMUactual = dtIMUavg = 1.0f/_ahrs->get_ins().get_sample_rate();
540 
541  // set number of updates over which gps and baro measurements are applied to the velocity and position states
542  gpsUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecGpsAvg);
543  gpsUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/gpsUpdateCountMaxInv);
544  hgtUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecHgtAvg);
545  hgtUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/hgtUpdateCountMaxInv);
546  magUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecMagAvg);
547  magUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/magUpdateCountMaxInv);
548  flowUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecFlowAvg);
549  flowUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/flowUpdateCountMaxInv);
550 
551  // calculate initial orientation and earth magnetic field states
552  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(_ahrs->roll, _ahrs->pitch);
553 
554  // write to state vector
555  state.gyro_bias.zero();
556  state.accel_zbias1 = 0;
557  state.accel_zbias2 = 0;
558  state.wind_vel.zero();
559 
560  // read the GPS and set the position and velocity states
561  readGpsData();
562  ResetVelocity();
563  ResetPosition();
564 
565  // read the barometer and set the height state
566  readHgtData();
567  ResetHeight();
568 
569  // set stored states to current state
570  StoreStatesReset();
571 
572  // set to true now that states have be initialised
573  statesInitialised = true;
574 
575  // define Earth rotation vector in the NED navigation frame
576  calcEarthRateNED(earthRateNED, _ahrs->get_home().lat);
577 
578  // initialise IMU pre-processing states
579  readIMUData();
580 
581  // initialise the covariance matrix
582  CovarianceInit();
583 
584  return true;
585 }
586 
587 // Initialise the states from accelerometer and magnetometer data (if present)
588 // This method can only be used when the vehicle is static
589 bool NavEKF::InitialiseFilterBootstrap(void)
590 {
591  // If we are a plane and don't have GPS lock then don't initialise
592  if (assume_zero_sideslip() && _ahrs->get_gps().status() < AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D) {
593  statesInitialised = false;
594  return false;
595  }
596 
597  // set re-used variables to zero
598  InitialiseVariables();
599 
600  // get initial time deltat between IMU measurements (sec)
601  dtIMUactual = dtIMUavg = 1.0f/_ahrs->get_ins().get_sample_rate();
602 
603  // set number of updates over which gps and baro measurements are applied to the velocity and position states
604  gpsUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecGpsAvg);
605  gpsUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/gpsUpdateCountMaxInv);
606  hgtUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecHgtAvg);
607  hgtUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/hgtUpdateCountMaxInv);
608  magUpdateCountMaxInv = (dtIMUavg * 1000.0f)/float(msecMagAvg);
609  magUpdateCountMax = uint8_t(1.0f/magUpdateCountMaxInv);
610 
611  // acceleration vector in XYZ body axes measured by the IMU (m/s^2)
612  Vector3f initAccVec;
613 
614  // TODO we should average accel readings over several cycles
615  initAccVec = _ahrs->get_ins().get_accel();
616 
617  // read the magnetometer data
618  readMagData();
619 
620  // normalise the acceleration vector
621  float pitch=0, roll=0;
622  if (initAccVec.length() > 0.001f) {
623  initAccVec.normalize();
624 
625  // calculate initial pitch angle
626  pitch = asinf(initAccVec.x);
627 
628  // calculate initial roll angle
629  roll = -asinf(initAccVec.y / cosf(pitch));
630  }
631 
632  // calculate initial orientation and earth magnetic field states
633  Quaternion initQuat;
634  initQuat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(roll, pitch);
635 
636  // check on ground status
637  SetFlightAndFusionModes();
638 
639  // write to state vector
640  state.quat = initQuat;
641  state.gyro_bias.zero();
642  state.accel_zbias1 = 0;
643  state.accel_zbias2 = 0;
644  state.wind_vel.zero();
645  state.body_magfield.zero();
646 
647  // read the GPS and set the position and velocity states
648  readGpsData();
649  ResetVelocity();
650  ResetPosition();
651 
652  // read the barometer and set the height state
653  readHgtData();
654  ResetHeight();
655 
656  // set stored states to current state
657  StoreStatesReset();
658 
659  // set to true now we have intialised the states
660  statesInitialised = true;
661 
662  // define Earth rotation vector in the NED navigation frame
663  calcEarthRateNED(earthRateNED, _ahrs->get_home().lat);
664 
665  // initialise IMU pre-processing states
666  readIMUData();
667 
668  // initialise the covariance matrix
669  CovarianceInit();
670 
671  return true;
672 }
673 
674 // Update Filter States - this should be called whenever new IMU data is available
675 void NavEKF::UpdateFilter()
676 {
677  // zero the delta quaternion used by the strapdown navigation because it is published
678  // and we need to return a zero rotation of the INS fails to update it
679  correctedDelAngQuat.initialise();
680 
681  // don't run filter updates if states have not been initialised
682  if (!statesInitialised) {
683  return;
684  }
685 
686  // start the timer used for load measurement
687  perf_begin(_perf_UpdateFilter);
688 
689  //get starting time for update step
690  imuSampleTime_ms = hal.scheduler->millis();
691 
692  // read IMU data and convert to delta angles and velocities
693  readIMUData();
694 
695  static bool prev_armed = false;
696  bool armed = getVehicleArmStatus();
697 
698  // the vehicle was previously disarmed and time has slipped
699  // gyro auto-zero has likely just been done - skip this timestep
700  if (!prev_armed && dtIMUactual > dtIMUavg*5.0f) {
701  // stop the timer used for load measurement
702  perf_end(_perf_UpdateFilter);
703  prev_armed = armed;
704  return;
705  }
706  prev_armed = armed;
707 
708  // detect if the filter update has been delayed for too long
709  if (dtIMUactual > 0.2f) {
710  // we have stalled for too long - reset states
711  ResetVelocity();
712  ResetPosition();
713  ResetHeight();
714  StoreStatesReset();
715  //Initialise IMU pre-processing states
716  readIMUData();
717  // stop the timer used for load measurement
718  perf_end(_perf_UpdateFilter);
719  return;
720  }
721 
722  // check if on ground
723  SetFlightAndFusionModes();
724 
725  // Check arm status and perform required checks and mode changes
726  performArmingChecks();
727 
728  // run the strapdown INS equations every IMU update
729  UpdateStrapdownEquationsNED();
730 
731  // store the predicted states for subsequent use by measurement fusion
732  StoreStates();
733 
734  // sum delta angles and time used by covariance prediction
735  summedDelAng = summedDelAng + correctedDelAng;
736  summedDelVel = summedDelVel + correctedDelVel1;
737  dt += dtIMUactual;
738 
739  // perform a covariance prediction if the total delta angle has exceeded the limit
740  // or the time limit will be exceeded at the next IMU update
741  if (((dt >= (covTimeStepMax - dtIMUactual)) || (summedDelAng.length() > covDelAngMax))) {
742  CovariancePrediction();
743  } else {
744  covPredStep = false;
745  }
746 
747  // Read range finder data which is used by both position and optical flow fusion
748  readRangeFinder();
749 
750  // Update states using GPS, altimeter, compass, airspeed and synthetic sideslip observations
751  SelectVelPosFusion();
752  SelectMagFusion();
753  SelectFlowFusion();
754  SelectTasFusion();
755  SelectBetaFusion();
756 
757  // stop the timer used for load measurement
758  perf_end(_perf_UpdateFilter);
759 }
760 
761 // select fusion of velocity, position and height measurements
762 void NavEKF::SelectVelPosFusion()
763 {
764  // check for and read new GPS data
765  readGpsData();
766 
767  // Specify which measurements should be used and check data for freshness
768  if (PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
769 
770  // check if we can use opticalflow as a backup
771  bool optFlowBackup = (flowDataValid && !hgtTimeout);
772 
773  // Set GPS time-out threshold depending on whether we have an airspeed sensor to constrain drift
774  uint16_t gpsRetryTimeout = useAirspeed() ? gpsRetryTimeUseTAS : gpsRetryTimeNoTAS;
775 
776  // Set the time that copters will fly without a GPS lock before failing the GPS and switching to a non GPS mode
777  uint16_t gpsFailTimeout = optFlowBackup ? gpsFailTimeWithFlow : gpsRetryTimeout;
778 
779  // If we haven't received GPS data for a while, then declare the position and velocity data as being timed out
780  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastFixTime_ms > gpsFailTimeout) {
781  posTimeout = true;
782  velTimeout = true;
783  // If this happens in flight and we don't have airspeed or sideslip assumption or optical flow to constrain drift, then go into constant position mode.
784  // Stay in that mode until the vehicle is re-armed.
785  // If we can do optical flow nav (valid flow data and hieght above ground estimate, then go into flow nav mode.
786  // Stay in that mode until the vehicle is dis-armed.
787  if (vehicleArmed && !useAirspeed() && !assume_zero_sideslip()) {
788  if (optFlowBackup) {
789  // we can do optical flow only nav
790  _fusionModeGPS = 3;
791  PV_AidingMode = AID_RELATIVE;
792  constVelMode = false;
793  constPosMode = false;
794  } else {
795  constVelMode = false; // always clear constant velocity mode if constant velocity mode is active
796  constPosMode = true;
797  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE;
798  posTimeout = true;
799  velTimeout = true;
800  // reset the velocity
801  ResetVelocity();
802  // store the current position to be used to keep reporting the last known position
803  lastKnownPositionNE.x = state.position.x;
804  lastKnownPositionNE.y = state.position.y;
805  // reset the position
806  ResetPosition();
807  }
808  // set the position and velocity timeouts to indicate we are not using GPS data
809  posTimeout = true;
810  velTimeout = true;
811  }
812  }
813 
814  // command fusion of GPS data and reset states as required
815  if (newDataGps && (PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE)) {
816  // reset data arrived flag
817  newDataGps = false;
818  // reset state updates and counter used to spread fusion updates across several frames to reduce 10Hz pulsing
819  memset(&gpsIncrStateDelta[0], 0, sizeof(gpsIncrStateDelta));
820  gpsUpdateCount = 0;
821  // use both if GPS use is enabled
822  fuseVelData = true;
823  fusePosData = true;
824  // If a long time since last GPS update, then reset position and velocity and reset stored state history
825  if (imuSampleTime_ms - secondLastFixTime_ms > gpsRetryTimeout) {
826  // Apply an offset to the GPS position so that the position can be corrected gradually
827  gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.x = statesAtPosTime.position.x - gpsPosNE.x;
828  gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.y = statesAtPosTime.position.y - gpsPosNE.y;
829  // limit the radius of the offset to 100m and decay the offset to zero radially
830  decayGpsOffset();
831  ResetPosition();
832  ResetVelocity();
833  // record the fail time
834  lastPosFailTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
835  // Reset the normalised innovation to avoid false failing the bad position fusion test
836  posTestRatio = 0.0f;
837  }
838  } else {
839  fuseVelData = false;
840  fusePosData = false;
841  }
842  } else if (constPosMode && covPredStep) {
843  // in constant position mode use synthetic position measurements set to zero
844  // only fuse synthetic measurements when rate of change of velocity is less than 0.5g to reduce attitude errors due to launch acceleration
845  // do not use velocity fusion to reduce the effect of movement on attitude
846  if (accNavMag < 4.9f) {
847  fusePosData = true;
848  } else {
849  fusePosData = false;
850  }
851  fuseVelData = false;
852  } else if (constVelMode && covPredStep) {
853  // In constant velocity mode we fuse the last valid velocity vector
854  // Reset the stored velocity vector when we enter the mode
855  if (constVelMode && !lastConstVelMode) {
856  heldVelNE.x = state.velocity.x;
857  heldVelNE.y = state.velocity.y;
858  }
859  lastConstVelMode = constVelMode;
860  // We do not fuse when manoeuvring to avoid corrupting the attitude
861  if (accNavMag < 4.9f) {
862  fuseVelData = true;
863  } else {
864  fuseVelData = false;
865  }
866  fusePosData = false;
867  } else {
868  fuseVelData = false;
869  fusePosData = false;
870  }
871 
872  // check for and read new height data
873  readHgtData();
874 
875  // If we haven't received height data for a while, then declare the height data as being timed out
876  // set timeout period based on whether we have vertical GPS velocity available to constrain drift
877  hgtRetryTime = (_fusionModeGPS == 0 && !velTimeout) ? hgtRetryTimeMode0 : hgtRetryTimeMode12;
878  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastHgtMeasTime > hgtRetryTime) {
879  hgtTimeout = true;
880  }
881 
882  // command fusion of height data
883  if (newDataHgt)
884  {
885  // reset data arrived flag
886  newDataHgt = false;
887  // reset state updates and counter used to spread fusion updates across several frames to reduce 10Hz pulsing
888  memset(&hgtIncrStateDelta[0], 0, sizeof(hgtIncrStateDelta));
889  hgtUpdateCount = 0;
890  // enable fusion
891  fuseHgtData = true;
892  } else {
893  fuseHgtData = false;
894  }
895 
896  // perform fusion
897  if (fuseVelData || fusePosData || fuseHgtData) {
898  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
899  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
900  FuseVelPosNED();
901  }
902 
903  // Fuse corrections to quaternion, position and velocity states across several time steps to reduce 5 and 10Hz pulsing in the output
904  if (gpsUpdateCount < gpsUpdateCountMax) {
905  gpsUpdateCount ++;
906  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
907  states[i] += gpsIncrStateDelta[i];
908  }
909  }
910  if (hgtUpdateCount < hgtUpdateCountMax) {
911  hgtUpdateCount ++;
912  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
913  states[i] += hgtIncrStateDelta[i];
914  }
915  }
916 
917  // Detect and declare bad GPS aiding status for minimum 10 seconds if a GPS rejection occurs after
918  // rejection of GPS and reset to GPS position. This addresses failure case where errors cause ongoing rejection
919  // of GPS and severe loss of position accuracy.
920  uint32_t gpsRetryTime;
921  if (useAirspeed()) {
922  gpsRetryTime = gpsRetryTimeUseTAS;
923  } else {
924  gpsRetryTime = gpsRetryTimeNoTAS;
925  }
926  if ((posTestRatio > 2.0f) && ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosFailTime) < gpsRetryTime) && ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosFailTime) > gpsRetryTime/2) && fusePosData) {
927  lastGpsAidBadTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
928  gpsAidingBad = true;
929  }
930  gpsAidingBad = gpsAidingBad && ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastGpsAidBadTime_ms) < 10000);
931 }
932 
933 // select fusion of magnetometer data
934 void NavEKF::SelectMagFusion()
935 {
936  // start performance timer
937  perf_begin(_perf_FuseMagnetometer);
938 
939  // check for and read new magnetometer measurements
940  readMagData();
941 
942  // If we are using the compass and the magnetometer has been unhealthy for too long we declare a timeout
943  if (magHealth) {
944  magTimeout = false;
945  lastHealthyMagTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
946  } else if ((imuSampleTime_ms - lastHealthyMagTime_ms) > magFailTimeLimit_ms && use_compass()) {
947  magTimeout = true;
948  }
949 
950  // determine if conditions are right to start a new fusion cycle
951  bool dataReady = statesInitialised && use_compass() && newDataMag;
952  if (dataReady) {
953  // reset state updates and counter used to spread fusion updates across several frames to reduce 10Hz pulsing
954  memset(&magIncrStateDelta[0], 0, sizeof(magIncrStateDelta));
955  magUpdateCount = 0;
956  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
957  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
958  // fuse the three magnetometer componenents sequentially
959  for (mag_state.obsIndex = 0; mag_state.obsIndex <= 2; mag_state.obsIndex++) FuseMagnetometer();
960  }
961 
962  // Fuse corrections to quaternion, position and velocity states across several time steps to reduce 10Hz pulsing in the output
963  if (magUpdateCount < magUpdateCountMax) {
964  magUpdateCount ++;
965  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
966  states[i] += magIncrStateDelta[i];
967  }
968  }
969 
970  // stop performance timer
971  perf_end(_perf_FuseMagnetometer);
972 }
973 
974 // select fusion of optical flow measurements
975 void NavEKF::SelectFlowFusion()
976 {
977  // start performance timer
978  perf_begin(_perf_FuseOptFlow);
979  // Perform Data Checks
980  // Check if the optical flow data is still valid
981  flowDataValid = ((imuSampleTime_ms - flowValidMeaTime_ms) < 1000);
982  // Check if the optical flow sensor has timed out
983  bool flowSensorTimeout = ((imuSampleTime_ms - flowValidMeaTime_ms) > 5000);
984  // Check if the fusion has timed out (flow measurements have been rejected for too long)
985  bool flowFusionTimeout = ((imuSampleTime_ms - prevFlowFuseTime_ms) > 5000);
986  // check is the terrain offset estimate is still valid
987  gndOffsetValid = ((imuSampleTime_ms - gndHgtValidTime_ms) < 5000);
988  // Perform tilt check
989  bool tiltOK = (Tnb_flow.c.z > DCM33FlowMin);
990  // Constrain measurements to zero if we are using optical flow and are on the ground
991  if (_fusionModeGPS == 3 && !takeOffDetected && vehicleArmed) {
992  flowRadXYcomp[0] = 0.0f;
993  flowRadXYcomp[1] = 0.0f;
994  flowRadXY[0] = 0.0f;
995  flowRadXY[1] = 0.0f;
996  omegaAcrossFlowTime.zero();
997  }
998  // If the flow measurements have been rejected for too long and we are relying on them, then revert to constant position mode
999  if ((flowSensorTimeout || flowFusionTimeout) && PV_AidingMode == AID_RELATIVE) {
1000  constVelMode = false; // always clear constant velocity mode if constant velocity mode is active
1001  constPosMode = true;
1002  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE;
1003  // reset the velocity
1004  ResetVelocity();
1005  // store the current position to be used to keep reporting the last known position
1006  lastKnownPositionNE.x = state.position.x;
1007  lastKnownPositionNE.y = state.position.y;
1008  // reset the position
1009  ResetPosition();
1010  }
1011  // if we do have valid flow measurements, fuse data into a 1-state EKF to estimate terrain height
1012  // we don't do terrain height estimation in optical flow only mode as the ground becomes our zero height reference
1013  if ((newDataFlow || newDataRng) && tiltOK) {
1014  // fuse range data into the terrain estimator if available
1015  fuseRngData = newDataRng;
1016  // fuse optical flow data into the terrain estimator if available and if there is no range data (range data is better)
1017  fuseOptFlowData = (newDataFlow && !fuseRngData);
1018  // Estimate the terrain offset (runs a one state EKF)
1019  EstimateTerrainOffset();
1020  // Indicate we have used the range data
1021  newDataRng = false;
1022  // we don't do subsequent fusion of optical flow data into the main filter if GPS is good and terrain offset data is invalid
1023  // because an invalid height above ground estimate will cause the optical flow measurements to fight the GPS
1024  if (!gpsNotAvailable && !gndOffsetValid) {
1025  // turn off fusion permissions
1026  // reset the flags to indicate that no new range finder or flow data is available for fusion
1027  newDataFlow = false;
1028  }
1029  }
1030 
1031  // Fuse optical flow data into the main filter
1032  // if the filter is initialised, we have data to fuse and the vehicle is not excessively tilted, then perform optical flow fusion
1033  if (flowDataValid && newDataFlow && tiltOK && !constPosMode)
1034  {
1035  // reset state updates and counter used to spread fusion updates across several frames to reduce 10Hz pulsing
1036  memset(&flowIncrStateDelta[0], 0, sizeof(flowIncrStateDelta));
1037  flowUpdateCount = 0;
1038  // Set the flow noise used by the fusion processes
1039  R_LOS = sq(max(_flowNoise, 0.05f));
1040  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
1041  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
1042  // Fuse the optical flow X and Y axis data into the main filter sequentially
1043  for (flow_state.obsIndex = 0; flow_state.obsIndex <= 1; flow_state.obsIndex++) FuseOptFlow();
1044  // reset flag to indicate that no new flow data is available for fusion
1045  newDataFlow = false;
1046  // indicate that flow fusion has been performed. This is used for load spreading.
1047  flowFusePerformed = true;
1048  }
1049 
1050  // Apply corrections to quaternion, position and velocity states across several time steps to reduce 10Hz pulsing in the output
1051  if (flowUpdateCount < flowUpdateCountMax) {
1052  flowUpdateCount ++;
1053  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 9; i++) {
1054  states[i] += flowIncrStateDelta[i];
1055  }
1056  }
1057  // stop the performance timer
1058  perf_end(_perf_FuseOptFlow);
1059 }
1060 
1061 // select fusion of true airspeed measurements
1062 void NavEKF::SelectTasFusion()
1063 {
1064  // get true airspeed measurement
1065  readAirSpdData();
1066 
1067  // If we haven't received airspeed data for a while, then declare the airspeed data as being timed out
1068  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastAirspeedUpdate > tasRetryTime) {
1069  tasTimeout = true;
1070  }
1071 
1072  // if the filter is initialised, wind states are not inhibited and we have data to fuse, then perform TAS fusion
1073  tasDataWaiting = (statesInitialised && !inhibitWindStates && newDataTas);
1074  if (tasDataWaiting)
1075  {
1076  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
1077  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
1078  FuseAirspeed();
1079  TASmsecPrev = imuSampleTime_ms;
1080  tasDataWaiting = false;
1081  newDataTas = false;
1082  }
1083 }
1084 
1085 // select fusion of synthetic sideslip measurements
1086 // synthetic sidelip fusion only works for fixed wing aircraft and relies on the average sideslip being close to zero
1087 // it requires a stable wind for best results and should not be used for aerobatic flight with manoeuvres that induce large sidslip angles (eg knife-edge, spins, etc)
1088 void NavEKF::SelectBetaFusion()
1089 {
1090  // set true when the fusion time interval has triggered
1091  bool f_timeTrigger = ((imuSampleTime_ms - BETAmsecPrev) >= msecBetaAvg);
1092  // set true when use of synthetic sideslip fusion is necessary because we have limited sensor data or are dead reckoning position
1093  bool f_required = !(use_compass() && useAirspeed() && posHealth);
1094  // set true when sideslip fusion is feasible (requires zero sideslip assumption to be valid and use of wind states)
1095  bool f_feasible = (assume_zero_sideslip() && !inhibitWindStates);
1096  // use synthetic sideslip fusion if feasible, required and enough time has lapsed since the last fusion
1097  if (f_feasible && f_required && f_timeTrigger) {
1098  // ensure that the covariance prediction is up to date before fusing data
1099  if (!covPredStep) CovariancePrediction();
1100  FuseSideslip();
1101  BETAmsecPrev = imuSampleTime_ms;
1102  }
1103 }
1104 
1105 // update the quaternion, velocity and position states using IMU measurements
1106 void NavEKF::UpdateStrapdownEquationsNED()
1107 {
1108  Vector3f delVelNav; // delta velocity vector calculated using a blend of IMU1 and IMU2 data
1109  Vector3f delVelNav1; // delta velocity vector calculated using IMU1 data
1110  Vector3f delVelNav2; // delta velocity vector calculated using IMU2 data
1111 
1112  // remove sensor bias errors
1113  correctedDelAng = dAngIMU - state.gyro_bias;
1114  correctedDelVel1 = dVelIMU1;
1115  correctedDelVel2 = dVelIMU2;
1116  correctedDelVel1.z -= state.accel_zbias1;
1117  correctedDelVel2.z -= state.accel_zbias2;
1118 
1119  // use weighted average of both IMU units for delta velocities
1120  correctedDelVel12 = correctedDelVel1 * IMU1_weighting + correctedDelVel2 * (1.0f - IMU1_weighting);
1121 
1122  // apply correction for earths rotation rate
1123  // % * - and + operators have been overloaded
1124  correctedDelAng = correctedDelAng - prevTnb * earthRateNED*dtIMUactual;
1125 
1126  // convert the rotation vector to its equivalent quaternion
1127  correctedDelAngQuat.from_axis_angle(correctedDelAng);
1128 
1129  // update the quaternion states by rotating from the previous attitude through
1130  // the delta angle rotation quaternion and normalise
1131  state.quat *= correctedDelAngQuat;
1132  state.quat.normalize();
1133 
1134  // calculate the body to nav cosine matrix
1135  Matrix3f Tbn_temp;
1136  state.quat.rotation_matrix(Tbn_temp);
1137  prevTnb = Tbn_temp.transposed();
1138 
1139  float delVelGravity1_z = GRAVITY_MSS*dtDelVel1;
1140  float delVelGravity2_z = GRAVITY_MSS*dtDelVel2;
1141  float delVelGravity_z = delVelGravity1_z * IMU1_weighting + delVelGravity2_z * (1.0f - IMU1_weighting);
1142 
1143  // transform body delta velocities to delta velocities in the nav frame
1144  // * and + operators have been overloaded
1145 
1146  // blended IMU calc
1147  delVelNav = Tbn_temp*correctedDelVel12;
1148  delVelNav.z += delVelGravity_z;
1149 
1150  // single IMU calcs
1151  delVelNav1 = Tbn_temp*correctedDelVel1;
1152  delVelNav1.z += delVelGravity1_z;
1153 
1154  delVelNav2 = Tbn_temp*correctedDelVel2;
1155  delVelNav2.z += delVelGravity2_z;
1156 
1157  // calculate the rate of change of velocity (used for launch detect and other functions)
1158  velDotNED = delVelNav / dtIMUactual;
1159 
1160  // apply a first order lowpass filter
1161  velDotNEDfilt = velDotNED * 0.05f + velDotNEDfilt * 0.95f;
1162 
1163  // calculate a magnitude of the filtered nav acceleration (required for GPS
1164  // variance estimation)
1165  accNavMag = velDotNEDfilt.length();
1166  accNavMagHoriz = pythagorous2(velDotNEDfilt.x , velDotNEDfilt.y);
1167 
1168  // save velocity for use in trapezoidal intergration for position calcuation
1169  Vector3f lastVelocity = state.velocity;
1170  Vector3f lastVel1 = state.vel1;
1171  Vector3f lastVel2 = state.vel2;
1172 
1173  // sum delta velocities to get velocity
1174  state.velocity += delVelNav;
1175  state.vel1 += delVelNav1;
1176  state.vel2 += delVelNav2;
1177 
1178  // apply a trapezoidal integration to velocities to calculate position
1179  state.position += (state.velocity + lastVelocity) * (dtIMUactual*0.5f);
1180  state.posD1 += (state.vel1.z + lastVel1.z) * (dtIMUactual*0.5f);
1181  state.posD2 += (state.vel2.z + lastVel2.z) * (dtIMUactual*0.5f);
1182 
1183  // capture current angular rate to augmented state vector for use by optical flow fusion
1184  state.omega = correctedDelAng / dtIMUactual;
1185 
1186  // LPF the yaw rate using a 1 second time constant yaw rate and determine if we are doing continual
1187  // fast rotations that can cause problems due to gyro scale factor errors.
1188  float alphaLPF = constrain_float(dtIMUactual, 0.0f, 1.0f);
1189  yawRateFilt += (state.omega.z - yawRateFilt)*alphaLPF;
1190  if (fabsf(yawRateFilt) > 1.0f) {
1191  highYawRate = true;
1192  } else {
1193  highYawRate = false;
1194  }
1195 
1196  // limit states to protect against divergence
1197  ConstrainStates();
1198 }
1199 
1200 // calculate the predicted state covariance matrix
1201 void NavEKF::CovariancePrediction()
1202 {
1203  perf_begin(_perf_CovariancePrediction);
1204  float windVelSigma; // wind velocity 1-sigma process noise - m/s
1205  float dAngBiasSigma;// delta angle bias 1-sigma process noise - rad/s
1206  float dVelBiasSigma;// delta velocity bias 1-sigma process noise - m/s
1207  float magEarthSigma;// earth magnetic field 1-sigma process noise
1208  float magBodySigma; // body magnetic field 1-sigma process noise
1209  float daxCov; // X axis delta angle variance rad^2
1210  float dayCov; // Y axis delta angle variance rad^2
1211  float dazCov; // Z axis delta angle variance rad^2
1212  float dvxCov; // X axis delta velocity variance (m/s)^2
1213  float dvyCov; // Y axis delta velocity variance (m/s)^2
1214  float dvzCov; // Z axis delta velocity variance (m/s)^2
1215  float dvx; // X axis delta velocity (m/s)
1216  float dvy; // Y axis delta velocity (m/s)
1217  float dvz; // Z axis delta velocity (m/s)
1218  float dax; // X axis delta angle (rad)
1219  float day; // Y axis delta angle (rad)
1220  float daz; // Z axis delta angle (rad)
1221  float q0; // attitude quaternion
1222  float q1; // attitude quaternion
1223  float q2; // attitude quaternion
1224  float q3; // attitude quaternion
1225  float dax_b; // X axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
1226  float day_b; // Y axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
1227  float daz_b; // Z axis delta angle measurement bias (rad)
1228  float dvz_b; // Z axis delta velocity measurement bias (rad)
1229 
1230  // calculate covariance prediction process noise
1231  // use filtered height rate to increase wind process noise when climbing or descending
1232  // this allows for wind gradient effects.
1233  // filter height rate using a 10 second time constant filter
1234  float alpha = 0.1f * dt;
1235  hgtRate = hgtRate * (1.0f - alpha) - state.velocity.z * alpha;
1236 
1237  // use filtered height rate to increase wind process noise when climbing or descending
1238  // this allows for wind gradient effects.
1239  if (!inhibitWindStates) {
1240  windVelSigma = dt * constrain_float(_windVelProcessNoise, 0.01f, 1.0f) * (1.0f + constrain_float(_wndVarHgtRateScale, 0.0f, 1.0f) * fabsf(hgtRate));
1241  } else {
1242  windVelSigma = 0.0f;
1243  }
1244  dAngBiasSigma = dt * constrain_float(_gyroBiasProcessNoise, 1e-7f, 1e-5f);
1245  dVelBiasSigma = dt * constrain_float(_accelBiasProcessNoise, 1e-5f, 1e-3f);
1246  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
1247  magEarthSigma = dt * constrain_float(_magEarthProcessNoise, 1e-4f, 1e-2f);
1248  magBodySigma = dt * constrain_float(_magBodyProcessNoise, 1e-4f, 1e-2f);
1249  } else {
1250  magEarthSigma = 0.0f;
1251  magBodySigma = 0.0f;
1252  }
1253  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=9; i++) processNoise[i] = 1.0e-9f;
1254  for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) processNoise[i] = dAngBiasSigma;
1255  // scale gyro bias noise when disarmed to allow for faster bias estimation
1256  for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) {
1257  processNoise[i] = dAngBiasSigma;
1258  if (!vehicleArmed) {
1259  processNoise[i] *= gyroBiasNoiseScaler;
1260  }
1261  }
1262  // if we are yawing rapidly, inhibit yaw gyro bias learning to prevent gyro scale factor errors from corrupting the bias estimate
1263  if (highYawRate) {
1264  processNoise[12] = 0.0f;
1265  P[12][12] = 0.0f;
1266  }
1267  // scale accel bias noise when disarmed to allow for faster bias estimation
1268  // inhibit bias estimation during takeoff with ground effect to prevent bad bias learning
1269  if (expectGndEffectTakeoff) {
1270  processNoise[13] = 0.0f;
1271  } else if (!vehicleArmed) {
1272  processNoise[13] = dVelBiasSigma * accelBiasNoiseScaler;
1273  } else {
1274  processNoise[13] = dVelBiasSigma;
1275  }
1276  for (uint8_t i=14; i<=15; i++) processNoise[i] = windVelSigma;
1277  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=18; i++) processNoise[i] = magEarthSigma;
1278  for (uint8_t i=19; i<=21; i++) processNoise[i] = magBodySigma;
1279  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=21; i++) processNoise[i] = sq(processNoise[i]);
1280 
1281  // set variables used to calculate covariance growth
1282  dvx = summedDelVel.x;
1283  dvy = summedDelVel.y;
1284  dvz = summedDelVel.z;
1285  dax = summedDelAng.x;
1286  day = summedDelAng.y;
1287  daz = summedDelAng.z;
1288  q0 = state.quat[0];
1289  q1 = state.quat[1];
1290  q2 = state.quat[2];
1291  q3 = state.quat[3];
1292  dax_b = state.gyro_bias.x;
1293  day_b = state.gyro_bias.y;
1294  daz_b = state.gyro_bias.z;
1295  dvz_b = IMU1_weighting * state.accel_zbias1 + (1.0f - IMU1_weighting) * state.accel_zbias2;
1296  _gyrNoise = constrain_float(_gyrNoise, 1e-3f, 5e-2f);
1297  daxCov = sq(dt*_gyrNoise);
1298  dayCov = sq(dt*_gyrNoise);
1299  // Account for 3% scale factor error on Z angular rate. This reduces chance of continuous fast rotations causing loss of yaw reference.
1300  dazCov = sq(dt*_gyrNoise) + sq(dt*0.03f*yawRateFilt);
1301  _accNoise = constrain_float(_accNoise, 5e-2f, 1.0f);
1302  dvxCov = sq(dt*_accNoise);
1303  dvyCov = sq(dt*_accNoise);
1304  dvzCov = sq(dt*_accNoise);
1305 
1306  // calculate the predicted covariance due to inertial sensor error propagation
1307  SF[0] = dvz - dvz_b;
1308  SF[1] = 2*q3*SF[0] + 2*dvx*q1 + 2*dvy*q2;
1309  SF[2] = 2*dvx*q3 - 2*q1*SF[0] + 2*dvy*q0;
1310  SF[3] = 2*q2*SF[0] + 2*dvx*q0 - 2*dvy*q3;
1311  SF[4] = day/2 - day_b/2;
1312  SF[5] = daz/2 - daz_b/2;
1313  SF[6] = dax/2 - dax_b/2;
1314  SF[7] = dax_b/2 - dax/2;
1315  SF[8] = daz_b/2 - daz/2;
1316  SF[9] = day_b/2 - day/2;
1317  SF[10] = 2*q0*SF[0];
1318  SF[11] = q1/2;
1319  SF[12] = q2/2;
1320  SF[13] = q3/2;
1321  SF[14] = 2*dvy*q1;
1322 
1323  SG[0] = q0/2;
1324  SG[1] = sq(q3);
1325  SG[2] = sq(q2);
1326  SG[3] = sq(q1);
1327  SG[4] = sq(q0);
1328  SG[5] = 2*q2*q3;
1329  SG[6] = 2*q1*q3;
1330  SG[7] = 2*q1*q2;
1331 
1332  SQ[0] = dvzCov*(SG[5] - 2*q0*q1)*(SG[1] - SG[2] - SG[3] + SG[4]) - dvyCov*(SG[5] + 2*q0*q1)*(SG[1] - SG[2] + SG[3] - SG[4]) + dvxCov*(SG[6] - 2*q0*q2)*(SG[7] + 2*q0*q3);
1333  SQ[1] = dvzCov*(SG[6] + 2*q0*q2)*(SG[1] - SG[2] - SG[3] + SG[4]) - dvxCov*(SG[6] - 2*q0*q2)*(SG[1] + SG[2] - SG[3] - SG[4]) + dvyCov*(SG[5] + 2*q0*q1)*(SG[7] - 2*q0*q3);
1334  SQ[2] = dvzCov*(SG[5] - 2*q0*q1)*(SG[6] + 2*q0*q2) - dvyCov*(SG[7] - 2*q0*q3)*(SG[1] - SG[2] + SG[3] - SG[4]) - dvxCov*(SG[7] + 2*q0*q3)*(SG[1] + SG[2] - SG[3] - SG[4]);
1335  SQ[3] = (dayCov*q1*SG[0])/2 - (dazCov*q1*SG[0])/2 - (daxCov*q2*q3)/4;
1336  SQ[4] = (dazCov*q2*SG[0])/2 - (daxCov*q2*SG[0])/2 - (dayCov*q1*q3)/4;
1337  SQ[5] = (daxCov*q3*SG[0])/2 - (dayCov*q3*SG[0])/2 - (dazCov*q1*q2)/4;
1338  SQ[6] = (daxCov*q1*q2)/4 - (dazCov*q3*SG[0])/2 - (dayCov*q1*q2)/4;
1339  SQ[7] = (dazCov*q1*q3)/4 - (daxCov*q1*q3)/4 - (dayCov*q2*SG[0])/2;
1340  SQ[8] = (dayCov*q2*q3)/4 - (daxCov*q1*SG[0])/2 - (dazCov*q2*q3)/4;
1341  SQ[9] = sq(SG[0]);
1342  SQ[10] = sq(q1);
1343 
1344  SPP[0] = SF[10] + SF[14] - 2*dvx*q2;
1345  SPP[1] = 2*q2*SF[0] + 2*dvx*q0 - 2*dvy*q3;
1346  SPP[2] = 2*dvx*q3 - 2*q1*SF[0] + 2*dvy*q0;
1347  SPP[3] = 2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3;
1348  SPP[4] = 2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3;
1349  SPP[5] = sq(q0) - sq(q1) - sq(q2) + sq(q3);
1350  SPP[6] = SF[13];
1351  SPP[7] = SF[12];
1352 
1353  nextP[0][0] = P[0][0] + P[1][0]*SF[7] + P[2][0]*SF[9] + P[3][0]*SF[8] + P[10][0]*SF[11] + P[11][0]*SPP[7] + P[12][0]*SPP[6] + (daxCov*SQ[10])/4 + SF[7]*(P[0][1] + P[1][1]*SF[7] + P[2][1]*SF[9] + P[3][1]*SF[8] + P[10][1]*SF[11] + P[11][1]*SPP[7] + P[12][1]*SPP[6]) + SF[9]*(P[0][2] + P[1][2]*SF[7] + P[2][2]*SF[9] + P[3][2]*SF[8] + P[10][2]*SF[11] + P[11][2]*SPP[7] + P[12][2]*SPP[6]) + SF[8]*(P[0][3] + P[1][3]*SF[7] + P[2][3]*SF[9] + P[3][3]*SF[8] + P[10][3]*SF[11] + P[11][3]*SPP[7] + P[12][3]*SPP[6]) + SF[11]*(P[0][10] + P[1][10]*SF[7] + P[2][10]*SF[9] + P[3][10]*SF[8] + P[10][10]*SF[11] + P[11][10]*SPP[7] + P[12][10]*SPP[6]) + SPP[7]*(P[0][11] + P[1][11]*SF[7] + P[2][11]*SF[9] + P[3][11]*SF[8] + P[10][11]*SF[11] + P[11][11]*SPP[7] + P[12][11]*SPP[6]) + SPP[6]*(P[0][12] + P[1][12]*SF[7] + P[2][12]*SF[9] + P[3][12]*SF[8] + P[10][12]*SF[11] + P[11][12]*SPP[7] + P[12][12]*SPP[6]) + (dayCov*sq(q2))/4 + (dazCov*sq(q3))/4;

1706  nextP[16][1] = P[16][1] + P[16][0]*SF[6] + P[16][2]*SF[5] + P[16][3]*SF[9] + P[16][11]*SPP[6] - P[16][12]*SPP[7] - (P[16][10]*q0)/2;
1707  nextP[16][2] = P[16][2] + P[16][0]*SF[4] + P[16][1]*SF[8] + P[16][3]*SF[6] + P[16][12]*SF[11] - P[16][10]*SPP[6] - (P[16][11]*q0)/2;
1708  nextP[16][3] = P[16][3] + P[16][0]*SF[5] + P[16][1]*SF[4] + P[16][2]*SF[7] - P[16][11]*SF[11] + P[16][10]*SPP[7] - (P[16][12]*q0)/2;
1709  nextP[16][4] = P[16][4] + P[16][1]*SF[1] + P[16][0]*SF[3] + P[16][2]*SPP[0] - P[16][3]*SPP[2] - P[16][13]*SPP[4];
1710  nextP[16][5] = P[16][5] + P[16][0]*SF[2] + P[16][2]*SF[1] + P[16][3]*SF[3] - P[16][1]*SPP[0] + P[16][13]*SPP[3];
1711  nextP[16][6] = P[16][6] + P[16][1]*SF[2] + P[16][3]*SF[1] + P[16][0]*SPP[0] - P[16][2]*SPP[1] - P[16][13]*SPP[5];
1712  nextP[16][7] = P[16][7] + P[16][4]*dt;

1736  nextP[17][9] = P[17][9] + P[17][6]*dt;
1737  nextP[17][10] = P[17][10];
1738  nextP[17][11] = P[17][11];
1739  nextP[17][12] = P[17][12];

1749  nextP[18][0] = P[18][0] + P[18][1]*SF[7] + P[18][2]*SF[9] + P[18][3]*SF[8] + P[18][10]*SF[11] + P[18][11]*SPP[7] + P[18][12]*SPP[6];

1769  nextP[18][20] = P[18][20];

1771  nextP[19][0] = P[19][0] + P[19][1]*SF[7] + P[19][2]*SF[9] + P[19][3]*SF[8] + P[19][10]*SF[11] + P[19][11]*SPP[7] + P[19][12]*SPP[6];
1772  nextP[19][1] = P[19][1] + P[19][0]*SF[6] + P[19][2]*SF[5] + P[19][3]*SF[9] + P[19][11]*SPP[6] - P[19][12]*SPP[7] - (P[19][10]*q0)/2;
1773  nextP[19][2] = P[19][2] + P[19][0]*SF[4] + P[19][1]*SF[8] + P[19][3]*SF[6] + P[19][12]*SF[11] - P[19][10]*SPP[6] - (P[19][11]*q0)/2;
1774  nextP[19][3] = P[19][3] + P[19][0]*SF[5] + P[19][1]*SF[4] + P[19][2]*SF[7] - P[19][11]*SF[11] + P[19][10]*SPP[7] - (P[19][12]*q0)/2;
1775  nextP[19][4] = P[19][4] + P[19][1]*SF[1] + P[19][0]*SF[3] + P[19][2]*SPP[0] - P[19][3]*SPP[2] - P[19][13]*SPP[4];
1776  nextP[19][5] = P[19][5] + P[19][0]*SF[2] + P[19][2]*SF[1] + P[19][3]*SF[3] - P[19][1]*SPP[0] + P[19][13]*SPP[3];
1777  nextP[19][6] = P[19][6] + P[19][1]*SF[2] + P[19][3]*SF[1] + P[19][0]*SPP[0] - P[19][2]*SPP[1] - P[19][13]*SPP[5];
1778  nextP[19][7] = P[19][7] + P[19][4]*dt;
1779  nextP[19][8] = P[19][8] + P[19][5]*dt;

1794  nextP[20][1] = P[20][1] + P[20][0]*SF[6] + P[20][2]*SF[5] + P[20][3]*SF[9] + P[20][11]*SPP[6] - P[20][12]*SPP[7] - (P[20][10]*q0)/2;
1795  nextP[20][2] = P[20][2] + P[20][0]*SF[4] + P[20][1]*SF[8] + P[20][3]*SF[6] + P[20][12]*SF[11] - P[20][10]*SPP[6] - (P[20][11]*q0)/2;

1797  nextP[20][4] = P[20][4] + P[20][1]*SF[1] + P[20][0]*SF[3] + P[20][2]*SPP[0] - P[20][3]*SPP[2] - P[20][13]*SPP[4];
1798  nextP[20][5] = P[20][5] + P[20][0]*SF[2] + P[20][2]*SF[1] + P[20][3]*SF[3] - P[20][1]*SPP[0] + P[20][13]*SPP[3];
1799  nextP[20][6] = P[20][6] + P[20][1]*SF[2] + P[20][3]*SF[1] + P[20][0]*SPP[0] - P[20][2]*SPP[1] - P[20][13]*SPP[5];
1800  nextP[20][7] = P[20][7] + P[20][4]*dt;
1801  nextP[20][8] = P[20][8] + P[20][5]*dt;
1802  nextP[20][9] = P[20][9] + P[20][6]*dt;
1803  nextP[20][10] = P[20][10];
1804  nextP[20][11] = P[20][11];
1805  nextP[20][12] = P[20][12];
1806  nextP[20][13] = P[20][13];
1807  nextP[20][14] = P[20][14];
1808  nextP[20][15] = P[20][15];
1809  nextP[20][16] = P[20][16];
1810  nextP[20][17] = P[20][17];
1811  nextP[20][18] = P[20][18];
1812  nextP[20][19] = P[20][19];
1813  nextP[20][20] = P[20][20];
1814  nextP[20][21] = P[20][21];
1815  nextP[21][0] = P[21][0] + P[21][1]*SF[7] + P[21][2]*SF[9] + P[21][3]*SF[8] + P[21][10]*SF[11] + P[21][11]*SPP[7] + P[21][12]*SPP[6];
1816  nextP[21][1] = P[21][1] + P[21][0]*SF[6] + P[21][2]*SF[5] + P[21][3]*SF[9] + P[21][11]*SPP[6] - P[21][12]*SPP[7] - (P[21][10]*q0)/2;
1817  nextP[21][2] = P[21][2] + P[21][0]*SF[4] + P[21][1]*SF[8] + P[21][3]*SF[6] + P[21][12]*SF[11] - P[21][10]*SPP[6] - (P[21][11]*q0)/2;
1818  nextP[21][3] = P[21][3] + P[21][0]*SF[5] + P[21][1]*SF[4] + P[21][2]*SF[7] - P[21][11]*SF[11] + P[21][10]*SPP[7] - (P[21][12]*q0)/2;
1819  nextP[21][4] = P[21][4] + P[21][1]*SF[1] + P[21][0]*SF[3] + P[21][2]*SPP[0] - P[21][3]*SPP[2] - P[21][13]*SPP[4];
1820  nextP[21][5] = P[21][5] + P[21][0]*SF[2] + P[21][2]*SF[1] + P[21][3]*SF[3] - P[21][1]*SPP[0] + P[21][13]*SPP[3];
1821  nextP[21][6] = P[21][6] + P[21][1]*SF[2] + P[21][3]*SF[1] + P[21][0]*SPP[0] - P[21][2]*SPP[1] - P[21][13]*SPP[5];
1822  nextP[21][7] = P[21][7] + P[21][4]*dt;
1823  nextP[21][8] = P[21][8] + P[21][5]*dt;
1824  nextP[21][9] = P[21][9] + P[21][6]*dt;
1825  nextP[21][10] = P[21][10];
1826  nextP[21][11] = P[21][11];
1827  nextP[21][12] = P[21][12];
1828  nextP[21][13] = P[21][13];
1829  nextP[21][14] = P[21][14];
1830  nextP[21][15] = P[21][15];
1831  nextP[21][16] = P[21][16];
1832  nextP[21][17] = P[21][17];
1833  nextP[21][18] = P[21][18];
1834  nextP[21][19] = P[21][19];
1835  nextP[21][20] = P[21][20];
1836  nextP[21][21] = P[21][21];
1837 
1838  // add the general state process noise variances
1839  for (uint8_t i=0; i<= 21; i++)
1840  {
1841  nextP[i][i] = nextP[i][i] + processNoise[i];
1842  }
1843 
1844  // if the total position variance exceeds 1e4 (100m), then stop covariance
1845  // growth by setting the predicted to the previous values
1846  // This prevent an ill conditioned matrix from occurring for long periods
1847  // without GPS
1848  if ((P[7][7] + P[8][8]) > 1e4f)
1849  {
1850  for (uint8_t i=7; i<=8; i++)
1851  {
1852  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=21; j++)
1853  {
1854  nextP[i][j] = P[i][j];
1855  nextP[j][i] = P[j][i];
1856  }
1857  }
1858  }
1859 
1860  // copy covariances to output and fix numerical errors
1861  CopyAndFixCovariances();
1862 
1863  // constrain diagonals to prevent ill-conditioning
1864  ConstrainVariances();
1865 
1866  // set the flag to indicate that covariance prediction has been performed and reset the increments used by the covariance prediction
1867  covPredStep = true;
1868  summedDelAng.zero();
1869  summedDelVel.zero();
1870  dt = 0.0f;
1871 
1872  perf_end(_perf_CovariancePrediction);
1873 }
1874 
1875 // fuse selected position, velocity and height measurements
1876 void NavEKF::FuseVelPosNED()
1877 {
1878  // start performance timer
1879  perf_begin(_perf_FuseVelPosNED);
1880 
1881  // health is set bad until test passed
1882  velHealth = false;
1883  posHealth = false;
1884  hgtHealth = false;
1885 
1886  // declare variables used to check measurement errors
1887  Vector3f velInnov;
1888  Vector3f velInnov1;
1889  Vector3f velInnov2;
1890 
1891  // declare variables used to control access to arrays
1892  bool fuseData[6] = {false,false,false,false,false,false};
1893  uint8_t stateIndex;
1894  uint8_t obsIndex;
1895 
1896  // declare variables used by state and covariance update calculations
1897  float posErr;
1898  Vector6 R_OBS; // Measurement variances used for fusion
1899  Vector6 R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS; // Measurement variances used for data checks only
1900  Vector6 observation;
1901  float SK;
1902 
1903  // perform sequential fusion of GPS measurements. This assumes that the
1904  // errors in the different velocity and position components are
1905  // uncorrelated which is not true, however in the absence of covariance
1906  // data from the GPS receiver it is the only assumption we can make
1907  // so we might as well take advantage of the computational efficiencies
1908  // associated with sequential fusion
1909  if (fuseVelData || fusePosData || fuseHgtData) {
1910 
1911  // if constant position or constant velocity mode use the current states to calculate the predicted
1912  // measurement rather than use states from a previous time. We need to do this
1913  // because there may be no stored states due to lack of real measurements.
1914  if (constPosMode) {
1915  statesAtPosTime = state;
1916  } else if (constVelMode) {
1917  statesAtVelTime = state;
1918  }
1919 
1920  // set the GPS data timeout depending on whether airspeed data is present
1921  uint32_t gpsRetryTime;
1922  if (useAirspeed()) gpsRetryTime = gpsRetryTimeUseTAS;
1923  else gpsRetryTime = gpsRetryTimeNoTAS;
1924 
1925  // form the observation vector and zero velocity and horizontal position observations if in constant position mode
1926  // If in constant velocity mode, hold the last known horizontal velocity vector
1927  if (!constPosMode && !constVelMode) {
1928  observation[0] = velNED.x + gpsVelGlitchOffset.x;
1929  observation[1] = velNED.y + gpsVelGlitchOffset.y;
1930  observation[2] = velNED.z;
1931  observation[3] = gpsPosNE.x + gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.x;
1932  observation[4] = gpsPosNE.y + gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.y;
1933  } else if (constPosMode){
1934  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=4; i++) observation[i] = 0.0f;
1935  } else if (constVelMode) {
1936  observation[0] = heldVelNE.x;
1937  observation[1] = heldVelNE.y;
1938  for (uint8_t i=2; i<=4; i++) observation[i] = 0.0f;
1939  }
1940  observation[5] = -hgtMea;
1941 
1942  // calculate additional error in GPS position caused by manoeuvring
1943  posErr = gpsPosVarAccScale * accNavMag;
1944 
1945  // estimate the GPS Velocity, GPS horiz position and height measurement variances.
1946  // if the GPS is able to report a speed error, we use it to adjust the observation noise for GPS velocity
1947  // otherwise we scale it using manoeuvre acceleration
1948  if (gpsSpdAccuracy > 0.0f) {
1949  // use GPS receivers reported speed accuracy - floor at value set by gps noise parameter
1950  R_OBS[0] = sq(constrain_float(gpsSpdAccuracy, _gpsHorizVelNoise, 50.0f));
1951  R_OBS[2] = sq(constrain_float(gpsSpdAccuracy, _gpsVertVelNoise, 50.0f));
1952  } else {
1953  // calculate additional error in GPS velocity caused by manoeuvring
1954  R_OBS[0] = sq(constrain_float(_gpsHorizVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f)) + sq(gpsNEVelVarAccScale * accNavMag);
1955  R_OBS[2] = sq(constrain_float(_gpsVertVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f)) + sq(gpsDVelVarAccScale * accNavMag);
1956  }
1957  R_OBS[1] = R_OBS[0];
1958  R_OBS[3] = sq(constrain_float(_gpsHorizPosNoise, 0.1f, 10.0f)) + sq(posErr);
1959  R_OBS[4] = R_OBS[3];
1960  R_OBS[5] = sq(constrain_float(_baroAltNoise, 0.1f, 10.0f));
1961 
1962  // reduce weighting (increase observation noise) on baro if we are likely to be in ground effect
1963  if ((getTakeoffExpected() || getTouchdownExpected()) && vehicleArmed) {
1964  R_OBS[5] *= gndEffectBaroScaler;
1965  }
1966 
1967  // For data integrity checks we use the same measurement variances as used to calculate the Kalman gains for all measurements except GPS horizontal velocity
1968  // For horizontal GPs velocity we don't want the acceptance radius to increase with reported GPS accuracy so we use a value based on best GPs perfomrance
1969  // plus a margin for manoeuvres. It is better to reject GPS horizontal velocity errors early
1970  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=1; i++) R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[i] = sq(constrain_float(_gpsHorizVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f)) + sq(gpsNEVelVarAccScale * accNavMag);
1971  for (uint8_t i=2; i<=5; i++) R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[i] = R_OBS[i];
1972 
1973 
1974  // if vertical GPS velocity data is being used, check to see if the GPS vertical velocity and barometer
1975  // innovations have the same sign and are outside limits. If so, then it is likely aliasing is affecting
1976  // the accelerometers and we should disable the GPS and barometer innovation consistency checks.
1977  if (_fusionModeGPS == 0 && fuseVelData && (imuSampleTime_ms - lastHgtMeasTime) < (2 * msecHgtAvg)) {
1978  // calculate innovations for height and vertical GPS vel measurements
1979  float hgtErr = statesAtHgtTime.position.z - observation[5];
1980  float velDErr = statesAtVelTime.velocity.z - observation[2];
1981  // check if they are the same sign and both more than 3-sigma out of bounds
1982  if ((hgtErr*velDErr > 0.0f) && (sq(hgtErr) > 9.0f * (P[9][9] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[5])) && (sq(velDErr) > 9.0f * (P[6][6] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[2]))) {
1983  badIMUdata = true;
1984  } else {
1985  badIMUdata = false;
1986  }
1987  }
1988 
1989  // calculate innovations and check GPS data validity using an innovation consistency check
1990  // test position measurements
1991  if (fusePosData) {
1992  // test horizontal position measurements
1993  innovVelPos[3] = statesAtPosTime.position.x - observation[3];
1994  innovVelPos[4] = statesAtPosTime.position.y - observation[4];
1995  varInnovVelPos[3] = P[7][7] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[3];
1996  varInnovVelPos[4] = P[8][8] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[4];
1997  // apply an innovation consistency threshold test, but don't fail if bad IMU data
1998  // calculate max valid position innovation squared based on a maximum horizontal inertial nav accel error and GPS noise parameter
1999  // max inertial nav error is scaled with horizontal g to allow for increased errors when manoeuvring
2000  float accelScale = (1.0f + 0.1f * accNavMag);
2001  float maxPosInnov2 = sq(_gpsPosInnovGate * _gpsHorizPosNoise) + sq(0.005f * accelScale * float(_gpsGlitchAccelMax) * sq(0.001f * float(imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosPassTime)));
2002  posTestRatio = (sq(innovVelPos[3]) + sq(innovVelPos[4])) / maxPosInnov2;
2003  posHealth = ((posTestRatio < 1.0f) || badIMUdata);
2004  // declare a timeout condition if we have been too long without data or not aiding
2005  posTimeout = (((imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosPassTime) > gpsRetryTime) || PV_AidingMode == AID_NONE);
2006  // use position data if healthy, timed out, or in constant position mode
2007  if (posHealth || posTimeout || constPosMode) {
2008  posHealth = true;
2009  // only reset the failed time and do glitch timeout checks if we are doing full aiding
2010  if (PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
2011  lastPosPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
2012  // if timed out or outside the specified glitch radius, increment the offset applied to GPS data to compensate for large GPS position jumps
2013  if (posTimeout || (maxPosInnov2 > sq(float(_gpsGlitchRadiusMax)))) {
2014  gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.x += innovVelPos[3];
2015  gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.y += innovVelPos[4];
2016  // limit the radius of the offset and decay the offset to zero radially
2017  decayGpsOffset();
2018  // reset the position to the current GPS position which will include the glitch correction offset
2019  ResetPosition();
2020  // reset the velocity to the GPS velocity
2021  ResetVelocity();
2022  // don't fuse data on this time step
2023  fusePosData = false;
2024  // record the fail time
2025  lastPosFailTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
2026  // Reset the normalised innovation to avoid false failing the bad position fusion test
2027  posTestRatio = 0.0f;
2028  }
2029  }
2030  } else {
2031  posHealth = false;
2032  }
2033  }
2034 
2035  // test velocity measurements
2036  if (fuseVelData) {
2037  // test velocity measurements
2038  uint8_t imax = 2;
2039  if (_fusionModeGPS == 1 || constVelMode) {
2040  imax = 1;
2041  }
2042  float K1 = 0; // innovation to error ratio for IMU1
2043  float K2 = 0; // innovation to error ratio for IMU2
2044  float innovVelSumSq = 0; // sum of squares of velocity innovations
2045  float varVelSum = 0; // sum of velocity innovation variances
2046  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=imax; i++) {
2047  // velocity states start at index 4
2048  stateIndex = i + 4;
2049  // calculate innovations using blended and single IMU predicted states
2050  velInnov[i] = statesAtVelTime.velocity[i] - observation[i]; // blended
2051  velInnov1[i] = statesAtVelTime.vel1[i] - observation[i]; // IMU1
2052  velInnov2[i] = statesAtVelTime.vel2[i] - observation[i]; // IMU2
2053  // calculate innovation variance
2054  varInnovVelPos[i] = P[stateIndex][stateIndex] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[i];
2055  // calculate error weightings for single IMU velocity states using
2056  // observation error to normalise
2057  float R_hgt;
2058  if (i == 2) {
2059  R_hgt = sq(constrain_float(_gpsVertVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f));
2060  } else {
2061  R_hgt = sq(constrain_float(_gpsHorizVelNoise, 0.05f, 5.0f));
2062  }
2063  K1 += R_hgt / (R_hgt + sq(velInnov1[i]));
2064  K2 += R_hgt / (R_hgt + sq(velInnov2[i]));
2065  // sum the innovation and innovation variances
2066  innovVelSumSq += sq(velInnov[i]);
2067  varVelSum += varInnovVelPos[i];
2068  }
2069  // calculate weighting used by fuseVelPosNED to do IMU accel data blending
2070  // this is used to detect and compensate for aliasing errors with the accelerometers
2071  // provide for a first order lowpass filter to reduce noise on the weighting if required
2072  // set weighting to 0.5 when on ground to allow more rapid learning of bias errors without 'ringing' in bias estimates
2073  if (vehicleArmed) {
2074  IMU1_weighting = 1.0f * (K1 / (K1 + K2)) + 0.0f * IMU1_weighting; // filter currently inactive
2075  } else {
2076  IMU1_weighting = 0.5f;
2077  }
2078  // apply an innovation consistency threshold test, but don't fail if bad IMU data
2079  // calculate the test ratio
2080  velTestRatio = innovVelSumSq / (varVelSum * sq(_gpsVelInnovGate));
2081  // fail if the ratio is greater than 1
2082  velHealth = ((velTestRatio < 1.0f) || badIMUdata);
2083  // declare a timeout if we have not fused velocity data for too long or not aiding
2084  velTimeout = (((imuSampleTime_ms - lastVelPassTime) > gpsRetryTime) || PV_AidingMode == AID_NONE);
2085  // if data is healthy or in constant velocity mode we fuse it
2086  if (velHealth || velTimeout || constVelMode) {
2087  velHealth = true;
2088  // restart the timeout count
2089  lastVelPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
2090  } else if (velTimeout && !posHealth && PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
2091  // if data is not healthy and timed out and position is unhealthy and we are using aiding, we reset the velocity, but do not fuse data on this time step
2092  ResetVelocity();
2093  fuseVelData = false;
2094  } else {
2095  // if data is unhealthy and position is healthy, we do not fuse it
2096  velHealth = false;
2097  }
2098  }
2099 
2100  // test height measurements
2101  if (fuseHgtData) {
2102  // calculate height innovations
2103  innovVelPos[5] = statesAtHgtTime.position.z - observation[5];
2104 
2105  varInnovVelPos[5] = P[9][9] + R_OBS_DATA_CHECKS[5];
2106  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
2107  hgtTestRatio = sq(innovVelPos[5]) / (sq(_hgtInnovGate) * varInnovVelPos[5]);
2108  // fail if the ratio is > 1, but don't fail if bad IMU data
2109  hgtHealth = ((hgtTestRatio < 1.0f) || badIMUdata);
2110  hgtTimeout = (imuSampleTime_ms - lastHgtPassTime) > hgtRetryTime;
2111  // Fuse height data if healthy or timed out or in constant position mode
2112  if (hgtHealth || hgtTimeout || constPosMode) {
2113  hgtHealth = true;
2114  lastHgtPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
2115  // if timed out, reset the height, but do not fuse data on this time step
2116  if (hgtTimeout) {
2117  ResetHeight();
2118  fuseHgtData = false;
2119  }
2120  }
2121  else {
2122  hgtHealth = false;
2123  }
2124  }
2125 
2126  // set range for sequential fusion of velocity and position measurements depending on which data is available and its health
2127  if (fuseVelData && _fusionModeGPS == 0 && velHealth && !constPosMode && PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
2128  fuseData[0] = true;
2129  fuseData[1] = true;
2130  fuseData[2] = true;
2131  }
2132  if (fuseVelData && _fusionModeGPS == 1 && velHealth && !constPosMode && PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) {
2133  fuseData[0] = true;
2134  fuseData[1] = true;
2135  }
2136  if ((fusePosData && posHealth && PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE) || constPosMode) {
2137  fuseData[3] = true;
2138  fuseData[4] = true;
2139  }
2140  if ((fuseHgtData && hgtHealth) || constPosMode) {
2141  fuseData[5] = true;
2142  }
2143  if (constVelMode) {
2144  fuseData[0] = true;
2145  fuseData[1] = true;
2146  }
2147 
2148  // fuse measurements sequentially
2149  for (obsIndex=0; obsIndex<=5; obsIndex++) {
2150  if (fuseData[obsIndex]) {
2151  stateIndex = 4 + obsIndex;
2152  // calculate the measurement innovation, using states from a different time coordinate if fusing height data
2153  // adjust scaling on GPS measurement noise variances if not enough satellites
2154  if (obsIndex <= 2)
2155  {
2156  innovVelPos[obsIndex] = statesAtVelTime.velocity[obsIndex] - observation[obsIndex];
2157  R_OBS[obsIndex] *= sq(gpsNoiseScaler);
2158  }
2159  else if (obsIndex == 3 || obsIndex == 4) {
2160  innovVelPos[obsIndex] = statesAtPosTime.position[obsIndex-3] - observation[obsIndex];
2161  R_OBS[obsIndex] *= sq(gpsNoiseScaler);
2162  } else {
2163  innovVelPos[obsIndex] = statesAtHgtTime.position[obsIndex-3] - observation[obsIndex];
2164  if (obsIndex == 5) {
2165  static const float gndMaxBaroErr = 4.0f;
2166  static const float gndBaroInnovFloor = -0.5f;
2167 
2168  if(getTouchdownExpected()) {
2169  // when a touchdown is expected, floor the barometer innovation at gndBaroInnovFloor
2170  // constrain the correction between 0 and gndBaroInnovFloor+gndMaxBaroErr
2171  // this function looks like this:
2172  // |/
2173  //---------|---------
2174  // ____/|
2175  // / |
2176  // / |
2177  innovVelPos[5] += constrain_float(-innovVelPos[5]+gndBaroInnovFloor, 0.0f, gndBaroInnovFloor+gndMaxBaroErr);
2178  }
2179  }
2180  }
2181 
2182  // calculate the Kalman gain and calculate innovation variances
2183  varInnovVelPos[obsIndex] = P[stateIndex][stateIndex] + R_OBS[obsIndex];
2184  SK = 1.0f/varInnovVelPos[obsIndex];
2185  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=12; i++) {
2186  Kfusion[i] = P[i][stateIndex]*SK;
2187  }
2188  // Only height and height rate observations are used to update z accel bias estimate
2189  // Protect Kalman gain from ill-conditioning
2190  // Don't update Z accel bias if off-level by greater than 60 degrees to avoid scale factor error effects
2191  // Don't update if we are taking off with ground effect
2192  if ((obsIndex == 5 || obsIndex == 2) && prevTnb.c.z > 0.5f && !getTakeoffExpected()) {
2193  Kfusion[13] = constrain_float(P[13][stateIndex]*SK,-1.0f,0.0f);
2194  } else {
2195  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;
2196  }
2197  // inhibit wind state estimation by setting Kalman gains to zero
2198  if (!inhibitWindStates) {
2199  Kfusion[14] = P[14][stateIndex]*SK;
2200  Kfusion[15] = P[15][stateIndex]*SK;
2201  } else {
2202  Kfusion[14] = 0.0f;
2203  Kfusion[15] = 0.0f;
2204  }
2205  // inhibit magnetic field state estimation by setting Kalman gains to zero
2206  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2207  for (uint8_t i = 16; i<=21; i++) {
2208  Kfusion[i] = P[i][stateIndex]*SK;
2209  }
2210  } else {
2211  for (uint8_t i = 16; i<=21; i++) {
2212  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
2213  }
2214  }
2215  // Set the Kalman gain values for the single IMU states
2216  Kfusion[22] = Kfusion[13]; // IMU2 Z accel bias
2217  Kfusion[26] = Kfusion[9]; // IMU1 posD
2218  Kfusion[30] = Kfusion[9]; // IMU2 posD
2219  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=2; i++) {
2220  Kfusion[i+23] = Kfusion[i+4]; // IMU1 velNED
2221  Kfusion[i+27] = Kfusion[i+4]; // IMU2 velNED
2222  }
2223 
2224  // Correct states that have been predicted using single (not blended) IMU data
2225  if (obsIndex == 5){
2226  // Calculate height measurement innovations using single IMU states
2227  float hgtInnov1 = statesAtHgtTime.posD1 - observation[obsIndex];
2228  float hgtInnov2 = statesAtHgtTime.posD2 - observation[obsIndex];
2229 
2230  if (vehicleArmed) {
2231  // Correct single IMU prediction states using height measurement, limiting rate of change of bias to 0.005 m/s3
2232  float correctionLimit = 0.005f * dtIMUavg * dtVelPos;
2233  state.accel_zbias1 -= constrain_float(Kfusion[13] * hgtInnov1, -correctionLimit, correctionLimit); // IMU1 Z accel bias
2234  state.accel_zbias2 -= constrain_float(Kfusion[22] * hgtInnov2, -correctionLimit, correctionLimit); // IMU2 Z accel bias
2235  } else {
2236  // When disarmed, do not rate limit accel bias learning
2237  state.accel_zbias1 -= Kfusion[13] * hgtInnov1; // IMU1 Z accel bias
2238  state.accel_zbias2 -= Kfusion[22] * hgtInnov2; // IMU2 Z accel bias
2239  }
2240 
2241  for (uint8_t i = 23; i<=26; i++) {
2242  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * hgtInnov1; // IMU1 velNED,posD
2243  }
2244  for (uint8_t i = 27; i<=30; i++) {
2245  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * hgtInnov2; // IMU2 velNED,posD
2246  }
2247  } else if (obsIndex == 0 || obsIndex == 1 || obsIndex == 2) {
2248  // Correct single IMU prediction states using velocity measurements
2249  for (uint8_t i = 23; i<=26; i++) {
2250  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * velInnov1[obsIndex]; // IMU1 velNED,posD
2251  }
2252  for (uint8_t i = 27; i<=30; i++) {
2253  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * velInnov2[obsIndex]; // IMU2 velNED,posD
2254  }
2255  }
2256 
2257  // calculate state corrections and re-normalise the quaternions for states predicted using the blended IMU data
2258  // attitude, velocity and position corrections are spread across multiple prediction cycles between now
2259  // and the anticipated time for the next measurement.
2260  // Don't spread quaternion corrections if total angle change across predicted interval is going to exceed 0.1 rad
2261  // Don't apply corrections to Z bias state as this has been done already as part of the single IMU calculations
2262  bool highRates = ((gpsUpdateCountMax * correctedDelAng.length()) > 0.1f);
2263  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
2264  if (i != 13) {
2265  if ((i <= 3 && highRates) || i >= 10 || constPosMode || constVelMode) {
2266  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * innovVelPos[obsIndex];
2267  } else {
2268  if (obsIndex == 5) {
2269  hgtIncrStateDelta[i] -= Kfusion[i] * innovVelPos[obsIndex] * hgtUpdateCountMaxInv;
2270  } else {
2271  gpsIncrStateDelta[i] -= Kfusion[i] * innovVelPos[obsIndex] * gpsUpdateCountMaxInv;
2272  }
2273  }
2274  }
2275  }
2276  state.quat.normalize();
2277 
2278  // update the covariance - take advantage of direct observation of a single state at index = stateIndex to reduce computations
2279  // this is a numerically optimised implementation of standard equation P = (I - K*H)*P;
2280  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=21; i++) {
2281  for (uint8_t j= 0; j<=21; j++)
2282  {
2283  KHP[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * P[stateIndex][j];
2284  }
2285  }
2286  for (uint8_t i= 0; i<=21; i++) {
2287  for (uint8_t j= 0; j<=21; j++) {
2288  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
2289  }
2290  }
2291  }
2292  }
2293  }
2294 
2295  // force the covariance matrix to be symmetrical and limit the variances to prevent ill-condiioning.
2296  ForceSymmetry();
2297  ConstrainVariances();
2298 
2299  // stop performance timer
2300  perf_end(_perf_FuseVelPosNED);
2301 }
2302 
2303 // fuse magnetometer measurements and apply innovation consistency checks
2304 // fuse each axis on consecutive time steps to spread computional load
2305 void NavEKF::FuseMagnetometer()
2306 {
2307  // declarations
2308  ftype &q0 = mag_state.q0;
2309  ftype &q1 = mag_state.q1;
2310  ftype &q2 = mag_state.q2;
2311  ftype &q3 = mag_state.q3;
2312  ftype &magN = mag_state.magN;
2313  ftype &magE = mag_state.magE;
2314  ftype &magD = mag_state.magD;
2315  ftype &magXbias = mag_state.magXbias;
2316  ftype &magYbias = mag_state.magYbias;
2317  ftype &magZbias = mag_state.magZbias;
2318  uint8_t &obsIndex = mag_state.obsIndex;
2319  Matrix3f &DCM = mag_state.DCM;
2320  Vector3f &MagPred = mag_state.MagPred;
2321  ftype &R_MAG = mag_state.R_MAG;
2322  ftype *SH_MAG = &mag_state.SH_MAG[0];
2323  Vector22 H_MAG;
2324  Vector6 SK_MX;
2325  Vector6 SK_MY;
2326  Vector6 SK_MZ;
2327 
2328  // perform sequential fusion of magnetometer measurements.
2329  // this assumes that the errors in the different components are
2330  // uncorrelated which is not true, however in the absence of covariance
2331  // data fit is the only assumption we can make
2332  // so we might as well take advantage of the computational efficiencies
2333  // associated with sequential fusion
2334  // calculate observation jacobians and Kalman gains
2335  if (obsIndex == 0)
2336  {
2337  // copy required states to local variable names
2338  q0 = statesAtMagMeasTime.quat[0];
2339  q1 = statesAtMagMeasTime.quat[1];
2340  q2 = statesAtMagMeasTime.quat[2];
2341  q3 = statesAtMagMeasTime.quat[3];
2342  magN = statesAtMagMeasTime.earth_magfield[0];
2343  magE = statesAtMagMeasTime.earth_magfield[1];
2344  magD = statesAtMagMeasTime.earth_magfield[2];
2345  magXbias = statesAtMagMeasTime.body_magfield[0];
2346  magYbias = statesAtMagMeasTime.body_magfield[1];
2347  magZbias = statesAtMagMeasTime.body_magfield[2];
2348 
2349  // rotate predicted earth components into body axes and calculate
2350  // predicted measurements
2351  DCM[0][0] = q0*q0 + q1*q1 - q2*q2 - q3*q3;
2352  DCM[0][1] = 2*(q1*q2 + q0*q3);
2353  DCM[0][2] = 2*(q1*q3-q0*q2);
2354  DCM[1][0] = 2*(q1*q2 - q0*q3);
2355  DCM[1][1] = q0*q0 - q1*q1 + q2*q2 - q3*q3;
2356  DCM[1][2] = 2*(q2*q3 + q0*q1);
2357  DCM[2][0] = 2*(q1*q3 + q0*q2);
2358  DCM[2][1] = 2*(q2*q3 - q0*q1);
2359  DCM[2][2] = q0*q0 - q1*q1 - q2*q2 + q3*q3;
2360  MagPred[0] = DCM[0][0]*magN + DCM[0][1]*magE + DCM[0][2]*magD + magXbias;
2361  MagPred[1] = DCM[1][0]*magN + DCM[1][1]*magE + DCM[1][2]*magD + magYbias;
2362  MagPred[2] = DCM[2][0]*magN + DCM[2][1]*magE + DCM[2][2]*magD + magZbias;
2363 
2364  // scale magnetometer observation error with total angular rate
2365  R_MAG = sq(constrain_float(_magNoise, 0.01f, 0.5f)) + sq(magVarRateScale*dAngIMU.length() / dtIMUavg);
2366 
2367  // calculate observation jacobians
2368  SH_MAG[0] = 2*magD*q3 + 2*magE*q2 + 2*magN*q1;
2369  SH_MAG[1] = 2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2;
2370  SH_MAG[2] = 2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3;
2371  SH_MAG[3] = sq(q3);
2372  SH_MAG[4] = sq(q2);
2373  SH_MAG[5] = sq(q1);
2374  SH_MAG[6] = sq(q0);
2375  SH_MAG[7] = 2*magN*q0;
2376  SH_MAG[8] = 2*magE*q3;
2377  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) H_MAG[i] = 0;
2378  H_MAG[0] = SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2;
2379  H_MAG[1] = SH_MAG[0];
2380  H_MAG[2] = 2*magE*q1 - 2*magD*q0 - 2*magN*q2;
2381  H_MAG[3] = SH_MAG[2];
2382  H_MAG[16] = SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[6];
2383  H_MAG[17] = 2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2;
2384  H_MAG[18] = 2*q1*q3 - 2*q0*q2;
2385  H_MAG[19] = 1;
2386 
2387  // calculate Kalman gain
2388  float temp = (P[19][19] + R_MAG + P[1][19]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][19]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][19]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) - (2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2)*(P[19][2] + P[1][2]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][2]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][2]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][2]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][2]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][2]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][2]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + (SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)*(P[19][0] + P[1][0]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][0]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][0]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][0]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][0]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][0]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][0]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + SH_MAG[0]*(P[19][1] + P[1][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][1]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][1]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][1]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][1]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][1]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][1]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + SH_MAG[2]*(P[19][3] + P[1][3]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][3]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][3]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][3]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][3]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) - (SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6])*(P[19][16] + P[1][16]*SH_MAG[0] + P[3][16]*SH_MAG[2] - P[16][16]*(SH_MAG[3] + SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] - SH_MAG[6]) + P[17][16]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][16]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][16]*(2*magD*q0 - 2*magE*q1 + 2*magN*q2) + P[0][16]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + P[17][19]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[18][19]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - P[2][19]*(2*magD*q0 -
