2510  Kfusion[18] = SK_MY[0]*(P[18][20] + P[18][0]*SH_MAG[2] + P[18][1]*SH_MAG[1] + P[18][2]*SH_MAG[0] - P[18][3]*SK_MY[2] - P[18][17]*SK_MY[1] - P[18][16]*SK_MY[3] + P[18][18]*SK_MY[4]);
2511  Kfusion[19] = SK_MY[0]*(P[19][20] + P[19][0]*SH_MAG[2] + P[19][1]*SH_MAG[1] + P[19][2]*SH_MAG[0] - P[19][3]*SK_MY[2] - P[19][17]*SK_MY[1] - P[19][16]*SK_MY[3] + P[19][18]*SK_MY[4]);
2512  Kfusion[20] = SK_MY[0]*(P[20][20] + P[20][0]*SH_MAG[2] + P[20][1]*SH_MAG[1] + P[20][2]*SH_MAG[0] - P[20][3]*SK_MY[2] - P[20][17]*SK_MY[1] - P[20][16]*SK_MY[3] + P[20][18]*SK_MY[4]);
2513  Kfusion[21] = SK_MY[0]*(P[21][20] + P[21][0]*SH_MAG[2] + P[21][1]*SH_MAG[1] + P[21][2]*SH_MAG[0] - P[21][3]*SK_MY[2] - P[21][17]*SK_MY[1] - P[21][16]*SK_MY[3] + P[21][18]*SK_MY[4]);
2514  } else {
2515  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) {
2516  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
2517  }
2518  }
2519 
2520  // calculate the observation innovation variance
2521  varInnovMag[1] = 1.0f/SK_MY[0];
2522 
2523  // set flags to indicate to other processes that fusion has been performede and is required on the next frame
2524  // this can be used by other fusion processes to avoid fusing on the same frame as this expensive step
2525  magFusePerformed = true;
2526  magFuseRequired = true;
2527  }
2528  else if (obsIndex == 2) // we are now fusing the Z measurement
2529  {
2530  // calculate observation jacobians
2531  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) H_MAG[i] = 0;
2532  H_MAG[0] = SH_MAG[1];
2533  H_MAG[1] = 2*magN*q3 - 2*magE*q0 - 2*magD*q1;
2534  H_MAG[2] = SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2;
2535  H_MAG[3] = SH_MAG[0];
2536  H_MAG[16] = 2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3;
2537  H_MAG[17] = 2*q2*q3 - 2*q0*q1;
2538  H_MAG[18] = SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6];
2539  H_MAG[21] = 1;
2540 
2541  // calculate Kalman gain
2542  float temp = (P[21][21] + R_MAG + P[0][21]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][21]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][21]*(SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6]) - (2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3)*(P[21][1] + P[0][1]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][1]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][1]*(SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6]) + P[16][1]*(2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3) - P[17][1]*(2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3) - P[1][1]*(2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3) + P[2][1]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + (SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)*(P[21][2] + P[0][2]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][2]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][2]*(SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6]) + P[16][2]*(2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3) - P[17][2]*(2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3) - P[1][2]*(2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3) + P[2][2]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + SH_MAG[1]*(P[21][0] + P[0][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][0]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][0]*(SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6]) + P[16][0]*(2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3) - P[17][0]*(2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3) - P[1][0]*(2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3) + P[2][0]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + SH_MAG[0]*(P[21][3] + P[0][3]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][3]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][3]*(SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6]) + P[16][3]*(2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3) - P[17][3]*(2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3) - P[1][3]*(2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3) + P[2][3]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + (SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6])*(P[21][18] + P[0][18]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][18]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][18]*(SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6]) + P[16][18]*(2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3) - P[17][18]*(2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3) - P[1][18]*(2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3) + P[2][18]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + P[16][21]*(2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3) - P[17][21]*(2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3) - P[1][21]*(2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3) + (2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3)*(P[21][16] + P[0][16]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][16]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][16]*(SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6]) + P[16][16]*(2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3) - P[17][16]*(2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3) - P[1][16]*(2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3) + P[2][16]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) - (2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3)*(P[21][17] + P[0][17]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][17]*SH_MAG[0] + P[18][17]*(SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6]) + P[16][17]*(2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3) - P[17][17]*(2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3) - P[1][17]*(2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3) + P[2][17]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2)) + P[2][21]*(SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2));
2543  if (temp >= R_MAG) {
2544  SK_MZ[0] = 1.0f / temp;
2545  faultStatus.bad_zmag = false;
2546  } else {
2547  // the calculation is badly conditioned, so we cannot perform fusion on this step
2548  // we increase the state variances and try again next time
2549  P[21][21] += 0.1f*R_MAG;
2550  obsIndex = 3;
2551  faultStatus.bad_zmag = true;
2552  return;
2553  }
2554  SK_MZ[1] = SH_MAG[3] - SH_MAG[4] - SH_MAG[5] + SH_MAG[6];
2555  SK_MZ[2] = 2*magD*q1 + 2*magE*q0 - 2*magN*q3;
2556  SK_MZ[3] = SH_MAG[7] + SH_MAG[8] - 2*magD*q2;
2557  SK_MZ[4] = 2*q0*q1 - 2*q2*q3;
2558  SK_MZ[5] = 2*q0*q2 + 2*q1*q3;
2559  Kfusion[0] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[0][21] + P[0][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[0][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[0][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[0][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[0][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[0][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[0][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2560  Kfusion[1] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[1][21] + P[1][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[1][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[1][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[1][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[1][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[1][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[1][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2561  Kfusion[2] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[2][21] + P[2][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[2][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[2][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[2][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[2][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[2][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[2][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2562  Kfusion[3] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[3][21] + P[3][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[3][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[3][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[3][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[3][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[3][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[3][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2563  Kfusion[4] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[4][21] + P[4][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[4][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[4][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[4][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[4][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[4][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[4][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2564  Kfusion[5] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[5][21] + P[5][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[5][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[5][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[5][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[5][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[5][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[5][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2565  Kfusion[6] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[6][21] + P[6][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[6][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[6][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[6][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[6][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[6][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[6][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2566  Kfusion[7] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[7][21] + P[7][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[7][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[7][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[7][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[7][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[7][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[7][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2567  Kfusion[8] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[8][21] + P[8][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[8][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[8][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[8][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[8][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[8][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[8][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2568  Kfusion[9] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[9][21] + P[9][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[9][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[9][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[9][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[9][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[9][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[9][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2569  Kfusion[10] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[10][21] + P[10][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[10][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[10][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[10][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[10][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[10][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[10][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2570  Kfusion[11] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[11][21] + P[11][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[11][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[11][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[11][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[11][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[11][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[11][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2571  Kfusion[12] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[12][21] + P[12][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[12][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[12][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[12][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[12][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[12][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[12][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2572  // this term has been zeroed to improve stability of the Z accel bias
2573  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_MZ[0]*(P[13][21] + P[13][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[13][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[13][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[13][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[13][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[13][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[13][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2574  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit wind state estimation
2575  if (!inhibitWindStates) {
2576  Kfusion[14] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[14][21] + P[14][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[14][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[14][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[14][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[14][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[14][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[14][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2577  Kfusion[15] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[15][21] + P[15][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[15][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[15][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[15][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[15][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[15][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[15][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2578  } else {
2579  Kfusion[14] = 0.0f;
2580  Kfusion[15] = 0.0f;
2581  }
2582  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit magnetic field state estimation
2583  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2584  Kfusion[16] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[16][21] + P[16][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[16][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[16][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[16][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[16][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[16][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[16][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2585  Kfusion[17] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[17][21] + P[17][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[17][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[17][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[17][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[17][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[17][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[17][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2586  Kfusion[18] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[18][21] + P[18][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[18][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[18][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[18][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[18][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[18][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[18][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2587  Kfusion[19] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[19][21] + P[19][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[19][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[19][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[19][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[19][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[19][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[19][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2588  Kfusion[20] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[20][21] + P[20][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[20][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[20][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[20][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[20][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[20][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[20][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2589  Kfusion[21] = SK_MZ[0]*(P[21][21] + P[21][0]*SH_MAG[1] + P[21][3]*SH_MAG[0] - P[21][1]*SK_MZ[2] + P[21][2]*SK_MZ[3] + P[21][18]*SK_MZ[1] + P[21][16]*SK_MZ[5] - P[21][17]*SK_MZ[4]);
2590  } else {
2591  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) {
2592  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
2593  }
2594  }
2595 
2596  // calculate the observation innovation variance
2597  varInnovMag[2] = 1.0f/SK_MZ[0];
2598 
2599  // set flags to indicate to other processes that fusion has been performede and is required on the next frame
2600  // this can be used by other fusion processes to avoid fusing on the same frame as this expensive step
2601  magFusePerformed = true;
2602  magFuseRequired = false;
2603  }
2604  // calculate the measurement innovation
2605  innovMag[obsIndex] = MagPred[obsIndex] - magData[obsIndex];
2606  // calculate the innovation test ratio
2607  magTestRatio[obsIndex] = sq(innovMag[obsIndex]) / (sq(_magInnovGate) * varInnovMag[obsIndex]);
2608  // check the last values from all components and set magnetometer health accordingly
2609  magHealth = (magTestRatio[0] < 1.0f && magTestRatio[1] < 1.0f && magTestRatio[2] < 1.0f);
2610  // Don't fuse unless all componenets pass. The exception is if the bad health has timed out and we are not a fly forward vehicle
2611  // In this case we might as well try using the magnetometer, but with a reduced weighting
2612  if (magHealth || ((magTestRatio[obsIndex] < 1.0f) && !assume_zero_sideslip() && magTimeout)) {
2613  // Attitude, velocity and position corrections are averaged across multiple prediction cycles between now and the anticipated time for the next measurement.
2614  // Don't do averaging of quaternion state corrections if total angle change across predicted interval is going to exceed 0.1 rad
2615  bool highRates = ((magUpdateCountMax * correctedDelAng.length()) > 0.1f);
2616  // Calculate the number of averaging frames left to go. This is required becasue magnetometer fusion is applied across three consecutive prediction cycles
2617  // There is no point averaging if the number of cycles left is less than 2
2618  float minorFramesToGo = float(magUpdateCountMax) - float(magUpdateCount);
2619  // correct the state vector or store corrections to be applied incrementally
2620  for (uint8_t j= 0; j<=21; j++) {
2621  // If we are forced to use a bad compass in flight, we reduce the weighting by a factor of 4
2622  if (!magHealth && !constPosMode) {
2623  Kfusion[j] *= 0.25f;
2624  }
2625  // If in the air and there is no other form of heading reference or we are yawing rapidly which creates larger inertial yaw errors,
2626  // we strengthen the magnetometer attitude correction
2627  if (vehicleArmed && (constPosMode || highYawRate) && j <= 3) {
2628  Kfusion[j] *= 4.0f;
2629  }
2630  // We don't need to spread corrections for non-dynamic states or if we are in a constant postion mode
2631  // We can't spread corrections if there is not enough time remaining
2632  // We don't spread corrections to attitude states if we are rotating rapidly
2633  if ((j <= 3 && highRates) || j >= 10 || constPosMode || minorFramesToGo < 1.5f ) {
2634  states[j] = states[j] - Kfusion[j] * innovMag[obsIndex];
2635  } else {
2636  // scale the correction based on the number of averaging frames left to go
2637  magIncrStateDelta[j] -= Kfusion[j] * innovMag[obsIndex] * (magUpdateCountMaxInv * float(magUpdateCountMax) / minorFramesToGo);
2638  }
2639  }
2640  // normalise the quaternion states
2641  state.quat.normalize();
2642  // correct the covariance P = (I - K*H)*P
2643  // take advantage of the empty columns in KH to reduce the
2644  // number of operations
2645  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
2646  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=3; j++) {
2647  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_MAG[j];
2648  }
2649  for (uint8_t j = 4; j<=15; j++) {
2650  KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
2651  }
2652  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2653  for (uint8_t j = 16; j<=21; j++) {
2654  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_MAG[j];
2655  }
2656  } else {
2657  for (uint8_t j = 16; j<=21; j++) {
2658  KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
2659  }
2660  }
2661  }
2662  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
2663  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++) {
2664  KHP[i][j] = 0;
2665  for (uint8_t k = 0; k<=3; k++) {
2666  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
2667  }
2668  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
2669  for (uint8_t k = 16; k<=21; k++) {
2670  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
2671  }
2672  }
2673  }
2674  }
2675  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
2676  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++) {
2677  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
2678  }
2679  }
2680  }
2681 
2682  // force the covariance matrix to be symmetrical and limit the variances to prevent
2683  // ill-condiioning.
2684  ForceSymmetry();
2685  ConstrainVariances();
2686 }
2687 
2688 /*
2689 Estimation of terrain offset using a single state EKF
2690 The filter can fuse motion compensated optiocal flow rates and range finder measurements
2691 */
2692 void NavEKF::EstimateTerrainOffset()
2693 {
2694  // start performance timer
2695  perf_begin(_perf_OpticalFlowEKF);
2696 
2697  // constrain height above ground to be above range measured on ground
2698  float heightAboveGndEst = max((terrainState - state.position.z), rngOnGnd);
2699 
2700  // calculate a predicted LOS rate squared
2701  float velHorizSq = sq(state.velocity.x) + sq(state.velocity.y);
2702  float losRateSq = velHorizSq / sq(heightAboveGndEst);
2703 
2704  // don't update terrain offset state if there is no range finder and not generating enough LOS rate, or without GPS, as it is poorly observable
2705  if (!fuseRngData && (gpsNotAvailable || PV_AidingMode == AID_RELATIVE || velHorizSq < 25.0f || losRateSq < 0.01f || onGround)) {
2706  inhibitGndState = true;
2707  } else {
2708  inhibitGndState = false;
2709  // record the time we last updated the terrain offset state
2710  gndHgtValidTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
2711 
2712  // propagate ground position state noise each time this is called using the difference in position since the last observations and an RMS gradient assumption
2713  // limit distance to prevent intialisation afer bad gps causing bad numerical conditioning
2714  float distanceTravelledSq = sq(statesAtRngTime.position[0] - prevPosN) + sq(statesAtRngTime.position[1] - prevPosE);
2715  distanceTravelledSq = min(distanceTravelledSq, 100.0f);
2716  prevPosN = statesAtRngTime.position[0];
2717  prevPosE = statesAtRngTime.position[1];
2718 
2719  // in addition to a terrain gradient error model, we also have a time based error growth that is scaled using the gradient parameter
2720  float timeLapsed = min(0.001f * (imuSampleTime_ms - timeAtLastAuxEKF_ms), 1.0f);
2721  float Pincrement = (distanceTravelledSq * sq(0.01f*float(_gndGradientSigma))) + sq(float(_gndGradientSigma) * timeLapsed);
2722  Popt += Pincrement;
2723  timeAtLastAuxEKF_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
2724 
2725  // fuse range finder data
2726  if (fuseRngData) {
2727  // predict range
2728  float predRngMeas = max((terrainState - statesAtRngTime.position[2]),rngOnGnd) / Tnb_flow.c.z;
2729 
2730  // Copy required states to local variable names
2731  float q0 = statesAtRngTime.quat[0]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2732  float q1 = statesAtRngTime.quat[1]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2733  float q2 = statesAtRngTime.quat[2]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2734  float q3 = statesAtRngTime.quat[3]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2735 
2736  // Set range finder measurement noise variance. TODO make this a function of range and tilt to allow for sensor, alignment and AHRS errors
2737  float R_RNG = 0.5f;
2738 
2739  // calculate Kalman gain
2740  float SK_RNG = sq(q0) - sq(q1) - sq(q2) + sq(q3);
2741  float K_RNG = Popt/(SK_RNG*(R_RNG + Popt/sq(SK_RNG)));
2742 
2743  // Calculate the innovation variance for data logging
2744  varInnovRng = (R_RNG + Popt/sq(SK_RNG));
2745 
2746  // constrain terrain height to be below the vehicle
2747  terrainState = max(terrainState, statesAtRngTime.position[2] + rngOnGnd);
2748 
2749  // Calculate the measurement innovation
2750  innovRng = predRngMeas - rngMea;
2751 
2752  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
2753  auxRngTestRatio = sq(innovRng) / (sq(_rngInnovGate) * varInnovRng);
2754 
2755  // Check the innovation for consistency and don't fuse if > 5Sigma
2756  if ((sq(innovRng)*SK_RNG) < 25.0f)
2757  {
2758  // correct the state
2759  terrainState -= K_RNG * innovRng;
2760 
2761  // constrain the state
2762  terrainState = max(terrainState, statesAtRngTime.position[2] + rngOnGnd);
2763 
2764  // correct the covariance
2765  Popt = Popt - sq(Popt)/(SK_RNG*(R_RNG + Popt/sq(SK_RNG))*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) - sq(q2) + sq(q3)));
2766 
2767  // prevent the state variance from becoming negative
2768  Popt = max(Popt,0.0f);
2769 
2770  }
2771  }
2772 
2773  if (fuseOptFlowData) {
2774 
2775  Vector3f vel; // velocity of sensor relative to ground in NED axes
2776  Vector3f relVelSensor; // velocity of sensor relative to ground in sensor axes
2777  float losPred; // predicted optical flow angular rate measurement
2778  float q0 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[0]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2779  float q1 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[1]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2780  float q2 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[2]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2781  float q3 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[3]; // quaternion at optical flow measurement time
2782  float K_OPT;
2783  float H_OPT;
2784 
2785  // Correct velocities for GPS glitch recovery offset
2786  vel.x = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[0] - gpsVelGlitchOffset.x;
2787  vel.y = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[1] - gpsVelGlitchOffset.y;
2788  vel.z = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[2];
2789 
2790  // predict range to centre of image
2791  float flowRngPred = max((terrainState - statesAtFlowTime.position[2]),rngOnGnd) / Tnb_flow.c.z;
2792 
2793  // constrain terrain height to be below the vehicle
2794  terrainState = max(terrainState, statesAtFlowTime.position[2] + rngOnGnd);
2795 
2796  // calculate relative velocity in sensor frame
2797  relVelSensor = Tnb_flow*vel;
2798 
2799  // divide velocity by range, subtract body rates and apply scale factor to
2800  // get predicted sensed angular optical rates relative to X and Y sensor axes
2801  losPred = relVelSensor.length()/flowRngPred;
2802 
2803  // calculate innovations
2804  auxFlowObsInnov = losPred - sqrtf(sq(flowRadXYcomp[0]) + sq(flowRadXYcomp[1]));
2805 
2806  // calculate observation jacobian
2807  float t3 = sq(q0);
2808  float t4 = sq(q1);
2809  float t5 = sq(q2);
2810  float t6 = sq(q3);
2811  float t10 = q0*q3*2.0f;
2812  float t11 = q1*q2*2.0f;
2813  float t14 = t3+t4-t5-t6;
2814  float t15 = t14*vel.x;
2815  float t16 = t10+t11;
2816  float t17 = t16*vel.y;
2817  float t18 = q0*q2*2.0f;
2818  float t19 = q1*q3*2.0f;
2819  float t20 = t18-t19;
2820  float t21 = t20*vel.z;
2821  float t2 = t15+t17-t21;
2822  float t7 = t3-t4-t5+t6;
2823  float t8 = statesAtFlowTime.position[2]-terrainState;
2824  float t9 = 1.0f/sq(t8);
2825  float t24 = t3-t4+t5-t6;
2826  float t25 = t24*vel.y;
2827  float t26 = t10-t11;
2828  float t27 = t26*vel.x;
2829  float t28 = q0*q1*2.0f;
2830  float t29 = q2*q3*2.0f;
2831  float t30 = t28+t29;
2832  float t31 = t30*vel.z;
2833  float t12 = t25-t27+t31;
2834  float t13 = sq(t7);
2835  float t22 = sq(t2);
2836  float t23 = 1.0f/(t8*t8*t8);
2837  float t32 = sq(t12);
2838  H_OPT = 0.5f*(t13*t22*t23*2.0f+t13*t23*t32*2.0f)/sqrtf(t9*t13*t22+t9*t13*t32);
2839 
2840  // calculate innovation variances
2841  auxFlowObsInnovVar = H_OPT*Popt*H_OPT + R_LOS;
2842 
2843  // calculate Kalman gain
2844  K_OPT = Popt*H_OPT/auxFlowObsInnovVar;
2845 
2846  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
2847  auxFlowTestRatio = sq(auxFlowObsInnov) / (sq(_flowInnovGate) * auxFlowObsInnovVar);
2848 
2849  // don't fuse if optical flow data is outside valid range
2850  if (max(flowRadXY[0],flowRadXY[1]) < _maxFlowRate) {
2851 
2852  // correct the state
2853  terrainState -= K_OPT * auxFlowObsInnov;
2854 
2855  // constrain the state
2856  terrainState = max(terrainState, statesAtFlowTime.position[2] + rngOnGnd);
2857 
2858  // correct the covariance
2859  Popt = Popt - K_OPT * H_OPT * Popt;
2860 
2861  // prevent the state variances from becoming negative
2862  Popt = max(Popt,0.0f);
2863  }
2864  }
2865  }
2866 
2867  // stop the performance timer
2868  perf_end(_perf_OpticalFlowEKF);
2869 }
2870 
2871 void NavEKF::FuseOptFlow()
2872 {
2873  Vector22 H_LOS;
2874  Vector8 tempVar;
2875  Vector3f velNED_local;
2876  Vector3f relVelSensor;
2877 
2878  uint8_t &obsIndex = flow_state.obsIndex;
2879  ftype &q0 = flow_state.q0;
2880  ftype &q1 = flow_state.q1;
2881  ftype &q2 = flow_state.q2;
2882  ftype &q3 = flow_state.q3;
2883  ftype *SH_LOS = &flow_state.SH_LOS[0];
2884  ftype *SK_LOS = &flow_state.SK_LOS[0];
2885  ftype &vn = flow_state.vn;
2886  ftype &ve = flow_state.ve;
2887  ftype &vd = flow_state.vd;
2888  ftype &pd = flow_state.pd;
2889  ftype *losPred = &flow_state.losPred[0];
2890 
2891  // Copy required states to local variable names
2892  q0 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[0];
2893  q1 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[1];
2894  q2 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[2];
2895  q3 = statesAtFlowTime.quat[3];
2896  vn = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[0];
2897  ve = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[1];
2898  vd = statesAtFlowTime.velocity[2];
2899  pd = statesAtFlowTime.position[2];
2900  // Correct velocities for GPS glitch recovery offset
2901  velNED_local.x = vn - gpsVelGlitchOffset.x;
2902  velNED_local.y = ve - gpsVelGlitchOffset.y;
2903  velNED_local.z = vd;
2904 
2905  // constrain height above ground to be above range measured on ground
2906  float heightAboveGndEst = max((terrainState - pd), rngOnGnd);
2907  // Calculate observation jacobians and Kalman gains
2908  if (obsIndex == 0) {
2909  // calculate range from ground plain to centre of sensor fov assuming flat earth
2910  float range = constrain_float((heightAboveGndEst/Tnb_flow.c.z),rngOnGnd,1000.0f);
2911 
2912  // calculate relative velocity in sensor frame
2913  relVelSensor = Tnb_flow*velNED_local;
2914 
2915  // divide velocity by range to get predicted angular LOS rates relative to X and Y axes
2916  losPred[0] = relVelSensor.y/range;
2917  losPred[1] = -relVelSensor.x/range;
2918 
2919 
2920  // Calculate common expressions for observation jacobians
2921  SH_LOS[0] = sq(q0) - sq(q1) - sq(q2) + sq(q3);
2922  SH_LOS[1] = vn*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3)) - vd*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) + ve*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2);
2923  SH_LOS[2] = ve*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) + sq(q2) - sq(q3)) + vd*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) - vn*(2*q0*q3 - 2*q1*q2);
2924  SH_LOS[3] = -1.0f/heightAboveGndEst;
2925 
2926  // Calculate common expressions for Kalman gains
2927  // calculate innovation variance for Y axis observation
2928  varInnovOptFlow[1] = (R_LOS + (SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3])*(P[0][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[2][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[6][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - (P[9][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1])/sq(pd - terrainState) + P[4][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3))) + (SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3])*(P[0][1]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][1]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[2][1]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][1]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][1]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[6][1]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - (P[9][1]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1])/sq(pd - terrainState) + P[4][1]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3))) - (SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3])*(P[0][2]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][2]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[2][2]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][2]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][2]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[2][3]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][3]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][3]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[6][3]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - (P[9][3]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1])/sq(pd - terrainState) + P[4][3]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3))) + SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3))*(P[0][4]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][4]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[2][4]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][4]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][4]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[6][4]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][5]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[2][5]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][5]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][5]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[6][5]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - (P[9][5]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1])/sq(pd - terrainState) + P[4][5]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3))) - SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3)*(P[0][6]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][6]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[2][6]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][6]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][6]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[6][6]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - (P[9][6]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1])/sq(pd - terrainState) + P[4][6]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3))) - (SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1]*(P[0][9]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][9]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[2][9]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) + 2*q2*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[3][9]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q3*SH_LOS[1]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[5][9]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2) - P[6][9]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) - (P[9][9]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[1])/sq(pd - terrainState) + P[4][9]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3))))/sq(pd - terrainState));
2929  if (varInnovOptFlow[1] > R_LOS) {
2930  SK_LOS[0] = 1.0f/varInnovOptFlow[1];
2931  } else {
2932  SK_LOS[0] = 1.0f/R_LOS;
2933  }
2934  // calculate innovation variance for X axis observation
2935  varInnovOptFlow[0] = (R_LOS + (SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[2]*SH_LOS[3])*(P[0][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q1*vd + 2*q0*ve - 2*q3*vn) + 2*q0*SH_LOS[2]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[1][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*vd - 2*q1*ve + 2*q2*vn) - 2*q1*SH_LOS[2]*SH_LOS[3]) + P[2][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*vd + 2*q2*ve + 2*q1*vn) - 2*q2*SH_LOS[2]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[3][0]*(SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q3*ve - 2*q2*vd + 2*q0*vn) - 2*q3*SH_LOS[2]*SH_LOS[3]) - P[4][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q3 - 2*q1*q2) + P[6][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) - (P[9][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[2])/sq(pd - terrainState) + P[5][0]*SH_LOS[0]*SH_LOS[3]*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) + sq(q2) - 3036  Kfusion[1] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[1][0]*tempVar[0] + P[1][1]*tempVar[1] - P[1][2]*tempVar[2] + P[1][3]*tempVar[3] + P[1][5]*tempVar[4] - P[1][6]*tempVar[5] - P[1][9]*tempVar[6] + P[1][4]*tempVar[7]);
3037  Kfusion[2] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[2][0]*tempVar[0] + P[2][1]*tempVar[1] - P[2][2]*tempVar[2] + P[2][3]*tempVar[3] + P[2][5]*tempVar[4] - P[2][6]*tempVar[5] - P[2][9]*tempVar[6] + P[2][4]*tempVar[7]);
3038  Kfusion[3] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[3][0]*tempVar[0] + P[3][1]*tempVar[1] - P[3][2]*tempVar[2] + P[3][3]*tempVar[3] + P[3][5]*tempVar[4] - P[3][6]*tempVar[5] - P[3][9]*tempVar[6] + P[3][4]*tempVar[7]);
3039  Kfusion[4] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[4][0]*tempVar[0] + P[4][1]*tempVar[1] - P[4][2]*tempVar[2] + P[4][3]*tempVar[3] + P[4][5]*tempVar[4] - P[4][6]*tempVar[5] - P[4][9]*tempVar[6] + P[4][4]*tempVar[7]);
3040  Kfusion[5] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[5][0]*tempVar[0] + P[5][1]*tempVar[1] - P[5][2]*tempVar[2] + P[5][3]*tempVar[3] + P[5][5]*tempVar[4] - P[5][6]*tempVar[5] - P[5][9]*tempVar[6] + P[5][4]*tempVar[7]);
3041  // Don't allow optical flow measurements to modify vertical velocity as it can produce height offsets
3042  Kfusion[6] = 0.0f;//SK_LOS[0]*(P[6][0]*tempVar[0] + P[6][1]*tempVar[1] - P[6][2]*tempVar[2] + P[6][3]*tempVar[3] + P[6][5]*tempVar[4] - P[6][6]*tempVar[5] - P[6][9]*tempVar[6] + P[6][4]*tempVar[7]);
3043  Kfusion[7] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[7][0]*tempVar[0] + P[7][1]*tempVar[1] - P[7][2]*tempVar[2] + P[7][3]*tempVar[3] + P[7][5]*tempVar[4] - P[7][6]*tempVar[5] - P[7][9]*tempVar[6] + P[7][4]*tempVar[7]);
3044  Kfusion[8] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[8][0]*tempVar[0] + P[8][1]*tempVar[1] - P[8][2]*tempVar[2] + P[8][3]*tempVar[3] + P[8][5]*tempVar[4] - P[8][6]*tempVar[5] - P[8][9]*tempVar[6] + P[8][4]*tempVar[7]);
3045  // Don't allow optical flow measurements to modify vertical position as it can produce height offsets
3046  Kfusion[9] = 0.0f;//SK_LOS[0]*(P[9][0]*tempVar[0] + P[9][1]*tempVar[1] - P[9][2]*tempVar[2] + P[9][3]*tempVar[3] + P[9][5]*tempVar[4] - P[9][6]*tempVar[5] - P[9][9]*tempVar[6] + P[9][4]*tempVar[7]);
3047  Kfusion[10] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[10][0]*tempVar[0] + P[10][1]*tempVar[1] - P[10][2]*tempVar[2] + P[10][3]*tempVar[3] + P[10][5]*tempVar[4] - P[10][6]*tempVar[5] - P[10][9]*tempVar[6] + P[10][4]*tempVar[7]);
3048  Kfusion[11] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[11][0]*tempVar[0] + P[11][1]*tempVar[1] - P[11][2]*tempVar[2] + P[11][3]*tempVar[3] + P[11][5]*tempVar[4] - P[11][6]*tempVar[5] - P[11][9]*tempVar[6] + P[11][4]*tempVar[7]);
3049  Kfusion[12] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[12][0]*tempVar[0] + P[12][1]*tempVar[1] - P[12][2]*tempVar[2] + P[12][3]*tempVar[3] + P[12][5]*tempVar[4] - P[12][6]*tempVar[5] - P[12][9]*tempVar[6] + P[12][4]*tempVar[7]);
3050  // only height measurements are allowed to modify the Z bias state to improve the stability of the estimate
3051  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_LOS[0]*(P[13][0]*tempVar[0] + P[13][1]*tempVar[1] - P[13][2]*tempVar[2] + P[13][3]*tempVar[3] + P[13][5]*tempVar[4] - P[13][6]*tempVar[5] - P[13][9]*tempVar[6] + P[13][4]*tempVar[7]);
3052  if (inhibitWindStates) {
3053  Kfusion[14] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[14][0]*tempVar[0] + P[14][1]*tempVar[1] - P[14][2]*tempVar[2] + P[14][3]*tempVar[3] + P[14][5]*tempVar[4] - P[14][6]*tempVar[5] - P[14][9]*tempVar[6] + P[14][4]*tempVar[7]);
3054  Kfusion[15] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[15][0]*tempVar[0] + P[15][1]*tempVar[1] - P[15][2]*tempVar[2] + P[15][3]*tempVar[3] + P[15][5]*tempVar[4] - P[15][6]*tempVar[5] - P[15][9]*tempVar[6] + P[15][4]*tempVar[7]);
3055  } else {
3056  Kfusion[14] = 0.0f;
3057  Kfusion[15] = 0.0f;
3058  }
3059  if (inhibitMagStates) {
3060  Kfusion[16] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[16][0]*tempVar[0] + P[16][1]*tempVar[1] - P[16][2]*tempVar[2] + P[16][3]*tempVar[3] + P[16][5]*tempVar[4] - P[16][6]*tempVar[5] - P[16][9]*tempVar[6] + P[16][4]*tempVar[7]);
3061  Kfusion[17] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[17][0]*tempVar[0] + P[17][1]*tempVar[1] - P[17][2]*tempVar[2] + P[17][3]*tempVar[3] + P[17][5]*tempVar[4] - P[17][6]*tempVar[5] - P[17][9]*tempVar[6] + P[17][4]*tempVar[7]);
3062  Kfusion[18] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[18][0]*tempVar[0] + P[18][1]*tempVar[1] - P[18][2]*tempVar[2] + P[18][3]*tempVar[3] + P[18][5]*tempVar[4] - P[18][6]*tempVar[5] - P[18][9]*tempVar[6] + P[18][4]*tempVar[7]);
3063  Kfusion[19] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[19][0]*tempVar[0] + P[19][1]*tempVar[1] - P[19][2]*tempVar[2] + P[19][3]*tempVar[3] + P[19][5]*tempVar[4] - P[19][6]*tempVar[5] - P[19][9]*tempVar[6] + P[19][4]*tempVar[7]);
3064  Kfusion[20] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[20][0]*tempVar[0] + P[20][1]*tempVar[1] - P[20][2]*tempVar[2] + P[20][3]*tempVar[3] + P[20][5]*tempVar[4] - P[20][6]*tempVar[5] - P[20][9]*tempVar[6] + P[20][4]*tempVar[7]);
3065  Kfusion[21] = SK_LOS[0]*(P[21][0]*tempVar[0] + P[21][1]*tempVar[1] - P[21][2]*tempVar[2] + P[21][3]*tempVar[3] + P[21][5]*tempVar[4] - P[21][6]*tempVar[5] - P[21][9]*tempVar[6] + P[21][4]*tempVar[7]);
3066  } else {
3067  for (uint8_t i = 16; i <= 21; i++) {
3068  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
3069  }
3070  }
3071  // calculate innovation for Y observation
3072  innovOptFlow[1] = losPred[1] - flowRadXYcomp[1];
3073 
3074  }
3075 
3076  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
3077  flowTestRatio[obsIndex] = sq(innovOptFlow[obsIndex]) / (sq(_flowInnovGate) * varInnovOptFlow[obsIndex]);
3078 
3079  // Check the innovation for consistency and don't fuse if out of bounds or flow is too fast to be reliable
3080  if ((flowTestRatio[obsIndex]) < 1.0f && (flowRadXY[obsIndex] < _maxFlowRate)) {
3081  // record the last time both X and Y observations were accepted for fusion
3082  if (obsIndex == 0) {
3083  flowXfailed = false;
3084  } else if (!flowXfailed) {
3085  prevFlowFuseTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
3086  }
3087  // Attitude, velocity and position corrections are averaged across multiple prediction cycles between now and the anticipated time for the next measurement.
3088  // Don't do averaging of quaternion state corrections if total angle change across predicted interval is going to exceed 0.1 rad
3089  bool highRates = ((flowUpdateCountMax * correctedDelAng.length()) > 0.1f);
3090  // Calculate the number of averaging frames left to go.
3091  // There is no point averaging if the number of cycles left is less than 2
3092  float minorFramesToGo = float(flowUpdateCountMax) - float(flowUpdateCount);
3093  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++) {
3094  if ((i <= 3 && highRates) || i >= 10 || minorFramesToGo < 1.5f) {
3095  states[i] = states[i] - Kfusion[i] * innovOptFlow[obsIndex];
3096  } else {
3097  flowIncrStateDelta[i] -= Kfusion[i] * innovOptFlow[obsIndex] * (flowUpdateCountMaxInv * float(flowUpdateCountMax) / minorFramesToGo);
3098  }
3099  }
3100  // normalise the quaternion states
3101  state.quat.normalize();
3102  // correct the covariance P = (I - K*H)*P
3103  // take advantage of the empty columns in KH to reduce the
3104  // number of operations
3105  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 21; i++)
3106  {
3107  for (uint8_t j = 0; j <= 6; j++)
3108  {
3109  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_LOS[j];
3110  }
3111  for (uint8_t j = 7; j <= 8; j++)
3112  {
3113  KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3114  }
3115  KH[i][9] = Kfusion[i] * H_LOS[9];
3116  for (uint8_t j = 10; j <= 21; j++)
3117  {
3118  KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3119  }
3120  }
3121  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 21; i++)
3122  {
3123  for (uint8_t j = 0; j <= 21; j++)
3124  {
3125  KHP[i][j] = 0.0f;
3126  for (uint8_t k = 0; k <= 6; k++)
3127  {
3128  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3129  }
3130  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][9] * P[9][j];
3131  }
3132  }
3133  for (uint8_t i = 0; i <= 21; i++)
3134  {
3135  for (uint8_t j = 0; j <= 21; j++)
3136  {
3137  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
3138  }
3139  }
3140  } else if (obsIndex == 0) {
3141  // store the fact we have failed the X conponent so that a combined X and Y axis pass/fail can be calculated next time round
3142  flowXfailed = true;
3143  }
3144 
3145  ForceSymmetry();
3146  ConstrainVariances();
3147 
3148 }
3149 
3150 // fuse true airspeed measurements
3151 void NavEKF::FuseAirspeed()
3152 {
3153  // start performance timer
3154  perf_begin(_perf_FuseAirspeed);
3155 
3156  // declarations
3157  float vn;
3158  float ve;
3159  float vd;
3160  float vwn;
3161  float vwe;
3162  float EAS2TAS = _ahrs->get_EAS2TAS();
3163  const float R_TAS = sq(constrain_float(_easNoise, 0.5f, 5.0f) * constrain_float(EAS2TAS, 0.9f, 10.0f));
3164  Vector3f SH_TAS;
3165  float SK_TAS;
3166  Vector22 H_TAS;
3167  float VtasPred;
3168 
3169  // health is set bad until test passed
3170  tasHealth = false;
3171 
3172  // copy required states to local variable names
3173  vn = statesAtVtasMeasTime.velocity.x;
3174  ve = statesAtVtasMeasTime.velocity.y;
3175  vd = statesAtVtasMeasTime.velocity.z;
3176  vwn = statesAtVtasMeasTime.wind_vel.x;
3177  vwe = statesAtVtasMeasTime.wind_vel.y;
3178 
3179  // calculate the predicted airspeed, compensating for bias in GPS velocity when we are pulling a glitch offset back in
3180  VtasPred = pythagorous3((ve - gpsVelGlitchOffset.y - vwe) , (vn - gpsVelGlitchOffset.x - vwn) , vd);
3181  // perform fusion of True Airspeed measurement
3182  if (VtasPred > 1.0f)
3183  {
3184  // calculate observation jacobians
3185  SH_TAS[0] = 1.0f/VtasPred;
3186  SH_TAS[1] = (SH_TAS[0]*(2*ve - 2*vwe))/2;
3187  SH_TAS[2] = (SH_TAS[0]*(2*vn - 2*vwn))/2;
3188  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) H_TAS[i] = 0.0f;
3189  H_TAS[4] = SH_TAS[2];
3190  H_TAS[5] = SH_TAS[1];
3191  H_TAS[6] = vd*SH_TAS[0];
3192  H_TAS[14] = -SH_TAS[2];
3193  H_TAS[15] = -SH_TAS[1];
3194 
3195  // calculate Kalman gains
3196  float temp = (R_TAS + SH_TAS[2]*(P[4][4]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][4]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][4]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][4]*vd*SH_TAS[0]) + SH_TAS[1]*(P[4][5]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][5]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][5]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][5]*vd*SH_TAS[0]) - SH_TAS[2]*(P[4][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][14]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][14]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][14]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][14]*vd*SH_TAS[0]) - SH_TAS[1]*(P[4][15]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][15]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][15]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][15]*vd*SH_TAS[0]) + vd*SH_TAS[0]*(P[4][6]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][6]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][6]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][6]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]));
3197  if (temp >= R_TAS) {
3198  SK_TAS = 1.0f / temp;
3199  faultStatus.bad_airspeed = false;
3200  } else {
3201  // the calculation is badly conditioned, so we cannot perform fusion on this step
3202  // we increase the wind state variances and try again next time
3203  P[14][14] += 0.05f*R_TAS;
3204  P[15][15] += 0.05f*R_TAS;
3205  faultStatus.bad_airspeed = true;
3206  return;
3207  }
3208  Kfusion[0] = SK_TAS*(P[0][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[0][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[0][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[0][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[0][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3209  Kfusion[1] = SK_TAS*(P[1][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[1][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[1][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[1][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[1][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3210  Kfusion[2] = SK_TAS*(P[2][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[2][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[2][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[2][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[2][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3211  Kfusion[3] = SK_TAS*(P[3][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[3][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[3][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[3][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[3][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3212  Kfusion[4] = SK_TAS*(P[4][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[4][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[4][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[4][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[4][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3213  Kfusion[5] = SK_TAS*(P[5][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[5][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[5][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[5][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[5][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3214  Kfusion[6] = SK_TAS*(P[6][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[6][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[6][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[6][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[6][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3215  Kfusion[7] = SK_TAS*(P[7][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[7][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[7][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[7][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[7][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3216  Kfusion[8] = SK_TAS*(P[8][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[8][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[8][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[8][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[8][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3217  Kfusion[9] = SK_TAS*(P[9][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[9][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[9][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[9][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[9][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3218  Kfusion[10] = SK_TAS*(P[10][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[10][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[10][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[10][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[10][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3219  Kfusion[11] = SK_TAS*(P[11][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[11][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[11][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[11][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[11][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3220  Kfusion[12] = SK_TAS*(P[12][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[12][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[12][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[12][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[12][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3221  // this term has been zeroed to improve stability of the Z accel bias
3222  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_TAS*(P[13][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[13][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[13][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[13][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[13][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3223  Kfusion[14] = SK_TAS*(P[14][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[14][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[14][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[14][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[14][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3224  Kfusion[15] = SK_TAS*(P[15][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[15][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[15][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[15][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[15][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3225  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit magnetic field state estimation
3226  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
3227  Kfusion[16] = SK_TAS*(P[16][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[16][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[16][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[16][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[16][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3228  Kfusion[17] = SK_TAS*(P[17][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[17][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[17][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[17][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[17][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3229  Kfusion[18] = SK_TAS*(P[18][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[18][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[18][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[18][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[18][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3230  Kfusion[19] = SK_TAS*(P[19][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[19][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[19][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[19][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[19][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3231  Kfusion[20] = SK_TAS*(P[20][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[20][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[20][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[20][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[20][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3232  Kfusion[21] = SK_TAS*(P[21][4]*SH_TAS[2] - P[21][14]*SH_TAS[2] + P[21][5]*SH_TAS[1] - P[21][15]*SH_TAS[1] + P[21][6]*vd*SH_TAS[0]);
3233  } else {
3234  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) {
3235  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
3236  }
3237  }
3238 
3239  // calculate measurement innovation variance
3240  varInnovVtas = 1.0f/SK_TAS;
3241 
3242  // calculate measurement innovation
3243  innovVtas = VtasPred - VtasMeas;
3244 
3245  // calculate the innovation consistency test ratio
3246  tasTestRatio = sq(innovVtas) / (sq(_tasInnovGate) * varInnovVtas);
3247 
3248  // fail if the ratio is > 1, but don't fail if bad IMU data
3249  tasHealth = ((tasTestRatio < 1.0f) || badIMUdata);
3250  tasTimeout = (imuSampleTime_ms - lastTasPassTime) > tasRetryTime;
3251 
3252  // test the ratio before fusing data, forcing fusion if airspeed and position are timed out as we have no choice but to try and use airspeed to constrain error growth
3253  if (tasHealth || (tasTimeout && posTimeout))
3254  {
3255 
3256  // restart the counter
3257  lastTasPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
3258 
3259  // correct the state vector
3260  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=21; j++)
3261  {
3262  states[j] = states[j] - Kfusion[j] * innovVtas;
3263  }
3264 
3265  state.quat.normalize();
3266 
3267  // correct the covariance P = (I - K*H)*P
3268  // take advantage of the empty columns in H to reduce the number of operations
3269  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3270  {
3271  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=3; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3272  for (uint8_t j = 4; j<=6; j++)
3273  {
3274  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_TAS[j];
3275  }
3276  for (uint8_t j = 7; j<=13; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3277  for (uint8_t j = 14; j<=15; j++)
3278  {
3279  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_TAS[j];
3280  }
3281  for (uint8_t j = 16; j<=21; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3282  }
3283  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3284  {
3285  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++)
3286  {
3287  KHP[i][j] = 0;
3288  for (uint8_t k = 4; k<=6; k++)
3289  {
3290  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3291  }
3292  for (uint8_t k = 14; k<=15; k++)
3293  {
3294  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3295  }
3296  }
3297  }
3298  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3299  {
3300  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++)
3301  {
3302  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
3303  }
3304  }
3305  }
3306  }
3307 
3308  // force the covariance matrix to me symmetrical and limit the variances to prevent ill-condiioning.
3309  ForceSymmetry();
3310  ConstrainVariances();
3311 
3312  // stop performance timer
3313  perf_end(_perf_FuseAirspeed);
3314 }
3315 
3316 // fuse sythetic sideslip measurement of zero
3317 void NavEKF::FuseSideslip()
3318 {
3319  // start performance timer
3320  perf_begin(_perf_FuseSideslip);
3321 
3322  // declarations
3323  float q0;
3324  float q1;
3325  float q2;
3326  float q3;
3327  float vn;
3328  float ve;
3329  float vd;
3330  float vwn;
3331  float vwe;
3332  const float R_BETA = 0.03f; // assume a sideslip angle RMS of ~10 deg
3333  Vector13 SH_BETA;
3334  Vector8 SK_BETA;
3335  Vector3f vel_rel_wind;
3336  Vector22 H_BETA;
3337  float innovBeta;
3338 
3339  // copy required states to local variable names
3340  q0 = state.quat[0];
3341  q1 = state.quat[1];
3342  q2 = state.quat[2];
3343  q3 = state.quat[3];
3344  vn = state.velocity.x;
3345  ve = state.velocity.y;
3346  vd = state.velocity.z;
3347  vwn = state.wind_vel.x;
3348  vwe = state.wind_vel.y;
3349 
3350  // calculate predicted wind relative velocity in NED, compensating for offset in velcity when we are pulling a GPS glitch offset back in
3351  vel_rel_wind.x = vn - vwn - gpsVelGlitchOffset.x;
3352  vel_rel_wind.y = ve - vwe - gpsVelGlitchOffset.y;
3353  vel_rel_wind.z = vd;
3354 
3355  // rotate into body axes
3356  vel_rel_wind = prevTnb * vel_rel_wind;
3357 
3358  // perform fusion of assumed sideslip = 0
3359  if (vel_rel_wind.x > 5.0f)
3360  {
3361  // Calculate observation jacobians
3362  SH_BETA[0] = (vn - vwn)*(sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3)) - vd*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3) + (ve - vwe)*(2*q0*q3 + 2*q1*q2);
3363  if (fabsf(SH_BETA[0]) <= 1e-9f) {
3364  faultStatus.bad_sideslip = true;
3365  return;
3366  } else {
3367  faultStatus.bad_sideslip = false;
3368  }
3369  SH_BETA[1] = (ve - vwe)*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) + sq(q2) - sq(q3)) + vd*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) - (vn - vwn)*(2*q0*q3 - 2*q1*q2);
3370  SH_BETA[2] = vn - vwn;
3371  SH_BETA[3] = ve - vwe;
3372  SH_BETA[4] = 1/sq(SH_BETA[0]);
3373  SH_BETA[5] = 1/SH_BETA[0];
3374  SH_BETA[6] = SH_BETA[5]*(sq(q0) - sq(q1) + sq(q2) - sq(q3));
3375  SH_BETA[7] = sq(q0) + sq(q1) - sq(q2) - sq(q3);
3376  SH_BETA[8] = 2*q0*SH_BETA[3] - 2*q3*SH_BETA[2] + 2*q1*vd;
3377  SH_BETA[9] = 2*q0*SH_BETA[2] + 2*q3*SH_BETA[3] - 2*q2*vd;
3378  SH_BETA[10] = 2*q2*SH_BETA[2] - 2*q1*SH_BETA[3] + 2*q0*vd;
3379  SH_BETA[11] = 2*q1*SH_BETA[2] + 2*q2*SH_BETA[3] + 2*q3*vd;
3380  SH_BETA[12] = 2*q0*q3;
3381  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) {
3382  H_BETA[i] = 0.0f;
3383  }
3384  H_BETA[0] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[8] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[9];
3385  H_BETA[1] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[10] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[11];
3386  H_BETA[2] = SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[11] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[10];
3387  H_BETA[3] = - SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[9] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[8];
3388  H_BETA[4] = - SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7];
3389  H_BETA[5] = SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2);
3390  H_BETA[6] = SH_BETA[5]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(2*q0*q2 - 2*q1*q3);
3391  H_BETA[14] = SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7];
3392  H_BETA[15] = SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2) - SH_BETA[6];
3393

2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7]) + P[5][4]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) - P[15][4]*(SH_BETA[6] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(SH_BETA[12] + 2*q1*q2)) + P[0][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[8] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[9]) + P[1][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[10] - SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[11]) + P[2][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[11] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[10]) - P[3][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*SH_BETA[9] + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[8]) + P[6][4]*(SH_BETA[5]*(2*q0*q1 + 2*q2*q3) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*(2*q0*q2 - 3401  faultStatus.bad_sideslip = true;

3403  }
3404  SK_BETA[1] = SH_BETA[5]*(SH_BETA[12] - 2*q1*q2) + SH_BETA[1]*SH_BETA[4]*SH_BETA[7];

3413  Kfusion[2] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[2][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[2][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[2][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[2][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[2][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[2][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[2][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[2][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[2][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3414  Kfusion[3] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[3][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[3][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[3][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[3][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[3][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[3][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[3][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[3][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[3][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3415  Kfusion[4] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[4][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[4][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[4][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[4][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[4][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[4][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[4][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[4][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[4][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3416  Kfusion[5] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[5][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[5][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[5][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[5][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[5][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[5][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[5][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[5][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[5][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3417  Kfusion[6] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[6][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[6][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[6][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[6][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[6][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[6][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[6][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[6][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[6][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3418  Kfusion[7] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[7][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[7][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[7][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[7][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[7][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[7][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[7][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[7][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[7][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3419  Kfusion[8] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[8][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[8][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[8][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[8][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[8][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[8][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[8][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[8][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[8][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3420  Kfusion[9] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[9][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[9][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[9][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[9][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[9][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[9][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[9][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[9][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[9][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3421  Kfusion[10] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[10][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[10][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[10][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[10][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[10][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[10][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[10][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[10][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[10][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3422  Kfusion[11] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[11][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[11][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[11][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[11][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[11][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[11][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[11][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[11][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[11][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3423  Kfusion[12] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[12][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[12][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[12][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[12][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[12][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[12][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[12][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[12][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[12][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3424  // this term has been zeroed to improve stability of the Z accel bias
3425  Kfusion[13] = 0.0f;//SK_BETA[0]*(P[13][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[13][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[13][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[13][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[13][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[13][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[13][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[13][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[13][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3426  Kfusion[14] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[14][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[14][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[14][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[14][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[14][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[14][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[14][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[14][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[14][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3427  Kfusion[15] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[15][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[15][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[15][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[15][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[15][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[15][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[15][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[15][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[15][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3428  // zero Kalman gains to inhibit magnetic field state estimation
3429  if (!inhibitMagStates) {
3430  Kfusion[16] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[16][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[16][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[16][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[16][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[16][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[16][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[16][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[16][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[16][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3431  Kfusion[17] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[17][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[17][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[17][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[17][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[17][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[17][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[17][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[17][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[17][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3432  Kfusion[18] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[18][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[18][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[18][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[18][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[18][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[18][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[18][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[18][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[18][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3433  Kfusion[19] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[19][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[19][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[19][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[19][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[19][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[19][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[19][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[19][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[19][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3434  Kfusion[20] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[20][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[20][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[20][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[20][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[20][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[20][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[20][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[20][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[20][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3435  Kfusion[21] = SK_BETA[0]*(P[21][0]*SK_BETA[5] + P[21][1]*SK_BETA[4] - P[21][4]*SK_BETA[1] + P[21][5]*SK_BETA[2] + P[21][2]*SK_BETA[6] + P[21][6]*SK_BETA[3] - P[21][3]*SK_BETA[7] + P[21][14]*SK_BETA[1] - P[21][15]*SK_BETA[2]);
3436  } else {
3437  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) {
3438  Kfusion[i] = 0.0f;
3439  }
3440  }
3441 
3442  // calculate predicted sideslip angle and innovation using small angle approximation
3443  innovBeta = vel_rel_wind.y / vel_rel_wind.x;
3444 
3445  // reject measurement if greater than 3-sigma inconsistency
3446  if (innovBeta > 0.5f) {
3447  return;
3448  }
3449 
3450  // correct the state vector
3451  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=21; j++)
3452  {
3453  states[j] = states[j] - Kfusion[j] * innovBeta;
3454  }
3455 
3456  state.quat.normalize();
3457 
3458  // correct the covariance P = (I - K*H)*P
3459  // take advantage of the empty columns in H to reduce the
3460  // number of operations
3461  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3462  {
3463  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=6; j++)
3464  {
3465  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_BETA[j];
3466  }
3467  for (uint8_t j = 7; j<=13; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3468  for (uint8_t j = 14; j<=15; j++)
3469  {
3470  KH[i][j] = Kfusion[i] * H_BETA[j];
3471  }
3472  for (uint8_t j = 16; j<=21; j++) KH[i][j] = 0.0f;
3473  }
3474  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3475  {
3476  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++)
3477  {
3478  KHP[i][j] = 0;
3479  for (uint8_t k = 0; k<=6; k++)
3480  {
3481  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3482  }
3483  for (uint8_t k = 14; k<=15; k++)
3484  {
3485  KHP[i][j] = KHP[i][j] + KH[i][k] * P[k][j];
3486  }
3487  }
3488  }
3489  for (uint8_t i = 0; i<=21; i++)
3490  {
3491  for (uint8_t j = 0; j<=21; j++)
3492  {
3493  P[i][j] = P[i][j] - KHP[i][j];
3494  }
3495  }
3496  }
3497 
3498  // force the covariance matrix to me symmetrical and limit the variances to prevent ill-condiioning.
3499  ForceSymmetry();
3500  ConstrainVariances();
3501 
3502  // stop the performance timer
3503  perf_end(_perf_FuseSideslip);
3504 }
3505 
3506 // zero specified range of rows in the state covariance matrix
3507 void NavEKF::zeroRows(Matrix22 &covMat, uint8_t first, uint8_t last)
3508 {
3509  uint8_t row;
3510  for (row=first; row<=last; row++)
3511  {
3512  memset(&covMat[row][0], 0, sizeof(covMat[0][0])*22);
3513  }
3514 }
3515 
3516 // zero specified range of columns in the state covariance matrix
3517 void NavEKF::zeroCols(Matrix22 &covMat, uint8_t first, uint8_t last)
3518 {
3519  uint8_t row;
3520  for (row=0; row<=21; row++)
3521  {
3522  memset(&covMat[row][first], 0, sizeof(covMat[0][0])*(1+last-first));
3523  }
3524 }

3526 // store states in a history array along with time stamp
3527 void NavEKF::StoreStates()
3528 {
3529  // Don't need to store states more often than every 10 msec
3530  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastStateStoreTime_ms >= 10) {
3531  lastStateStoreTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
3532  if (storeIndex > 49) {
3533  storeIndex = 0;
3534  }
3535  storedStates[storeIndex] = state;
3536  statetimeStamp[storeIndex] = lastStateStoreTime_ms;
3537  storeIndex = storeIndex + 1;
3538  }
3539 }
3540 
3541 // reset the stored state history and store the current state
3542 void NavEKF::StoreStatesReset()
3543 {
3544  // clear stored state history
3545  memset(&storedStates[0], 0, sizeof(storedStates));
3546  memset(&statetimeStamp[0], 0, sizeof(statetimeStamp));
3547  // store current state vector in first column
3548  storeIndex = 0;
3549  storedStates[storeIndex] = state;
3550  statetimeStamp[storeIndex] = imuSampleTime_ms;
3551  storeIndex = storeIndex + 1;
3552 }
3553 
3554 // recall state vector stored at closest time to the one specified by msec
3555 void NavEKF::RecallStates(state_elements &statesForFusion, uint32_t msec)
3556 {
3557  uint32_t timeDelta;
3558  uint32_t bestTimeDelta = 200;
3559  uint8_t bestStoreIndex = 0;
3560  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++)
3561  {
3562  timeDelta = msec - statetimeStamp[i];
3563  if (timeDelta < bestTimeDelta)
3564  {
3565  bestStoreIndex = i;
3566  bestTimeDelta = timeDelta;
3567  }
3568  }
3569  if (bestTimeDelta < 200) // only output stored state if < 200 msec retrieval error
3570  {
3571  statesForFusion = storedStates[bestStoreIndex];
3572  }
3573  else // otherwise output current state
3574  {
3575  statesForFusion = state;
3576  }
3577 }
3578 
3579 // recall omega (angular rate vector) average across the time interval from msecStart to msecEnd
3580 void NavEKF::RecallOmega(Vector3f &omegaAvg, uint32_t msecStart, uint32_t msecEnd)
3581 {
3582  // calculate average angular rate vector over the time interval from msecStart to msecEnd
3583  // if no values are inside the time window, return the current angular rate
3584  omegaAvg.zero();
3585  uint8_t numAvg = 0;
3586  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=49; i++)
3587  {
3588  if (msecStart <= statetimeStamp[i] && msecEnd >= statetimeStamp[i])
3589  {
3590  omegaAvg += storedStates[i].omega;
3591  numAvg += 1;
3592  }
3593  }
3594  if (numAvg >= 1)
3595  {
3596  omegaAvg = omegaAvg / float(numAvg);
3597  } else if (dtIMUactual > 0) {
3598  omegaAvg = correctedDelAng / dtIMUactual;
3599  } else {
3600  omegaAvg.zero();
3601  }
3602 }

3606 {
3607  // Calculate the body to nav cosine matrix
3608  quat.rotation_matrix(Tbn);

3631 // Return the last calculated NED position relative to the reference point (m).
3632 // if a calculated solution is not available, use the best available data and return false
3633 bool NavEKF::getPosNED(Vector3f &pos) const
3634 {
3635  // The EKF always has a height estimate regardless of mode of operation
3636  pos.z = state.position.z;
3637  // There are three modes of operation, absolute position (GPS fusion), relative position (optical flow fusion) and constant position (no position estimate available)
3638  nav_filter_status status;
3639  getFilterStatus(status);
3640  if (status.flags.horiz_pos_abs || status.flags.horiz_pos_rel) {
3641  // This is the normal mode of operation where we can use the EKF position states
3642  pos.x = state.position.x;
3643  pos.y = state.position.y;
3644  return true;
3645  } else {
3646  // In constant position mode the EKF position states are at the origin, so we cannot use them as a position estimate
3647  if(validOrigin) {
3648  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().status() >= AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_2D)) {
3649  // If the origin has been set and we have GPS, then return the GPS position relative to the origin
3650  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location();
3651  Vector2f tempPosNE = location_diff(EKF_origin, gpsloc);
3652  pos.x = tempPosNE.x;
3653  pos.y = tempPosNE.y;
3654  return false;
3655  } else {
3656  // If no GPS fix is available, all we can do is provide the last known position
3657  pos.x = state.position.x + lastKnownPositionNE.x;
3658  pos.y = state.position.y + lastKnownPositionNE.y;
3659  return false;
3660  }
3661  } else {
3662  // If the origin has not been set, then we have no means of providing a relative position
3663  pos.x = 0.0f;
3664  pos.y = 0.0f;
3665  return false;
3666  }
3667  }
3668  return false;
3669 }

3671 // return body axis gyro bias estimates in rad/sec
3672 void NavEKF::getGyroBias(Vector3f &gyroBias) const
3673 {
3674  if (dtIMUavg < 1e-6f) {
3675  gyroBias.zero();

3677  }

3679 }

3681 // reset the body axis gyro bias states to zero and re-initialise the corresponding covariances
3682 void NavEKF::resetGyroBias(void)
3683 {
3684  state.gyro_bias.zero();
3685  zeroRows(P,10,12);
3686  zeroCols(P,10,12);
3687  P[10][10] = sq(radians(INIT_GYRO_BIAS_UNCERTAINTY * dtIMUavg));
3688  P[11][11] = P[10][10];
3689  P[12][12] = P[10][10];
3690 
3691 }

3693 // Commands the EKF to not use GPS.
3694 // This command must be sent prior to arming
3695 // This command is forgotten by the EKF each time the vehicle disarms
3696 // Returns 0 if command rejected
3697 // Returns 1 if attitude, vertical velocity and vertical position will be provided
3698 // Returns 2 if attitude, 3D-velocity, vertical position and relative horizontal position will be provided
3699 uint8_t NavEKF::setInhibitGPS(void)
3700 {
3701  if(!vehicleArmed) {
3702  return 0;
3703  }
3704  if (optFlowDataPresent()) {
3705  _fusionModeGPS = 3;
3706  return 2;
3707  } else {
3708  return 1;
3709  }
3710 }

3712 // return the horizontal speed limit in m/s set by optical flow sensor limits
3713 // return the scale factor to be applied to navigation velocity gains to compensate for increase in velocity noise with height when using optical flow
3714 void NavEKF::getEkfControlLimits(float &ekfGndSpdLimit, float &ekfNavVelGainScaler) const
3715 {
3716  if (PV_AidingMode == AID_RELATIVE) {
3717  // allow 1.0 rad/sec margin for angular motion
3718  ekfGndSpdLimit = max((_maxFlowRate - 1.0f), 0.0f) * max((terrainState - state.position[2]), rngOnGnd);
3719  // use standard gains up to 5.0 metres height and reduce above that
3720  ekfNavVelGainScaler = 4.0f / max((terrainState - state.position[2]),4.0f);
3721  } else {
3722  ekfGndSpdLimit = 400.0f; //return 80% of max filter speed
3723  ekfNavVelGainScaler = 1.0f;
3724  }
3725 }

3764 // return magnetometer offsets

3767 {

3778 // Return the last calculated latitude, longitude and height in WGS-84
3779 // If a calculated location isn't available, return a raw GPS measurement
3780 // The status will return true if a calculation or raw measurement is available
3781 // The getFilterStatus() function provides a more detailed description of data health and must be checked if data is to be used for flight control
3782 bool NavEKF::getLLH(struct Location &loc) const
3783 {
3784  if(validOrigin) {
3785  // Altitude returned is an absolute altitude relative to the WGS-84 spherioid
3786  loc.alt = EKF_origin.alt - state.position.z*100;
3787  loc.flags.relative_alt = 0;
3788  loc.flags.terrain_alt = 0;
3789 
3790  // there are three modes of operation, absolute position (GPS fusion), relative position (optical flow fusion) and constant position (no aiding)
3791  nav_filter_status status;
3792  getFilterStatus(status);
3793  if (status.flags.horiz_pos_abs || status.flags.horiz_pos_rel) {
3794  loc.lat = EKF_origin.lat;
3795  loc.lng = EKF_origin.lng;
3796  location_offset(loc, state.position.x, state.position.y);
3797  return true;
3798  } else {
3799  // we could be in constant position mode becasue the vehicle has taken off without GPS, or has lost GPS
3800  // in this mode we cannot use the EKF states to estimate position so will return the best available data
3801  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().status() >= AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_2D)) {
3802  // we have a GPS position fix to return
3803  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location();
3804  loc.lat = gpsloc.lat;
3805  loc.lng = gpsloc.lng;
3806  return true;
3807  } else {
3808  // if no GPS fix, provide last known position before entering the mode
3809  location_offset(loc, lastKnownPositionNE.x, lastKnownPositionNE.y);
3810  return false;
3811  }
3812  }
3813  } else {
3814  // If no origin has been defined for the EKF, then we cannot use its position states so return a raw
3815  // GPS reading if available and return false
3816  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().status() >= AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D)) {
3817  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location();
3818  loc = gpsloc;
3819  loc.flags.relative_alt = 0;
3820  loc.flags.terrain_alt = 0;
3821  }
3822  return false;
3823  }
3824 }
3825 
3826 // return the estimated height above ground level
3827 bool NavEKF::getHAGL(float &HAGL) const
3828 {
3829  HAGL = terrainState - state.position.z;
3830  // If we know the terrain offset and altitude, then we have a valid height above ground estimate
3831  return !hgtTimeout && gndOffsetValid && healthy();
3832 }

3834 // return data for debugging optical flow fusion
3835 void NavEKF::getFlowDebug(float &varFlow, float &gndOffset, float &flowInnovX, float &flowInnovY, float &auxInnov, float &HAGL, float &rngInnov, float &range, float &gndOffsetErr) const
3836 {
3837  varFlow = max(flowTestRatio[0],flowTestRatio[1]);
3838  gndOffset = terrainState;
3839  flowInnovX = innovOptFlow[0];
3840  flowInnovY = innovOptFlow[1];
3841  auxInnov = auxFlowObsInnov;
3842  HAGL = terrainState - state.position.z;
3843  rngInnov = innovRng;
3844  range = rngMea;
3845  gndOffsetErr = sqrtf(Popt); // note Popt is constrained to be non-negative in EstimateTerrainOffset()
3846 }

3848 // calculate whether the flight vehicle is on the ground or flying from height, airspeed and GPS speed
3849 void NavEKF::SetFlightAndFusionModes()
3850 {
3851  // determine if the vehicle is manoevring
3852  if (accNavMagHoriz > 0.5f){
3853  manoeuvring = true;
3854  } else {
3855  manoeuvring = false;
3856  }
3857  // if we are a fly forward type vehicle, then in-air mode can be determined through a combination of speed and height criteria
3858  if (assume_zero_sideslip()) {
3859  // Evaluate a numerical score that defines the likelihood we are in the air
3860  float gndSpdSq = sq(velNED[0]) + sq(velNED[1]);
3861  bool highGndSpd = false;
3862  bool highAirSpd = false;
3863  bool largeHgtChange = false;
3864 
3865  // trigger at 8 m/s airspeed
3866  if (_ahrs->airspeed_sensor_enabled()) {
3867  const AP_Airspeed *airspeed = _ahrs->get_airspeed();
3868  if (airspeed->get_airspeed() * airspeed->get_EAS2TAS() > 10.0f) {
3869  highAirSpd = true;
3870  }
3871  }
3872 
3873  // trigger at 10 m/s GPS velocity, but not if GPS is reporting bad velocity errors
3874  if (gndSpdSq > 100.0f && gpsSpdAccuracy < 1.0f) {
3875  highGndSpd = true;
3876  }
3877 
3878  // trigger if more than 10m away from initial height
3879  if (fabsf(hgtMea) > 10.0f) {
3880  largeHgtChange = true;
3881  }
3882 
3883  // to go to in-air mode we also need enough GPS velocity to be able to calculate a reliable ground track heading and either a lerge height or airspeed change
3884  if (onGround && highGndSpd && (highAirSpd || largeHgtChange)) {
3885  onGround = false;
3886  }
3887  // if is possible we are in flight, set the time this condition was last detected
3888  if (highGndSpd || highAirSpd || largeHgtChange) {
3889  airborneDetectTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
3890  }
3891  // after 5 seconds of not detecting a possible flight condition, we transition to on-ground mode
3892  if(!onGround && ((imuSampleTime_ms - airborneDetectTime_ms) > 5000)) {
3893  onGround = true;
3894  }
3895  // perform a yaw alignment check against GPS if exiting on-ground mode, bu tonly if we have enough ground speed
3896  // this is done to protect against unrecoverable heading alignment errors due to compass faults
3897  if (!onGround && prevOnGround) {
3898  alignYawGPS();
3899  }
3900  // If we aren't using an airspeed sensor we set the wind velocity to the reciprocal
3901  // of the velocity vector and scale states so that the wind speed is equal to 3m/s. This helps prevent gains
3902  // being too high at the start of flight if launching into a headwind until the first turn when the EKF can form
3903  // a wind speed estimate and also corrects bad initial wind estimates due to heading errors
3904  if (!onGround && prevOnGround && !useAirspeed()) {
3905  setWindVelStates();
3906  }
3907  }
3908  // store current on-ground status for next time
3909  prevOnGround = onGround;
3910  // If we are on ground, or in constant position mode, or don't have the right vehicle and sensing to estimate wind, inhibit wind states
3911  inhibitWindStates = ((!useAirspeed() && !assume_zero_sideslip()) || onGround || constPosMode);
3912  // request mag calibration for both in-air and manoeuvre threshold options
3913  bool magCalRequested = ((_magCal == 0) && !onGround) || ((_magCal == 1) && manoeuvring) || (_magCal == 3);
3914  // deny mag calibration request if we aren't using the compass, are in the pre-arm constant position mode or it has been inhibited by the user
3915  bool magCalDenied = !use_compass() || constPosMode || (_magCal == 2);
3916  // inhibit the magnetic field calibration if not requested or denied
3917  inhibitMagStates = (!magCalRequested || magCalDenied);
3918 }
3919 
3920 // initialise the covariance matrix
3921 void NavEKF::CovarianceInit()
3922 {
3923  // zero the matrix
3924  for (uint8_t i=1; i<=21; i++)
3925  {
3926  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=21; j++)
3927  {
3928  P[i][j] = 0.0f;
3929  }
3930  }
3931  // quaternions - TODO better maths for initial quaternion covariances that uses roll, pitch and yaw
3932  P[0][0] = 1.0e-9f;
3933  P[1][1] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
3934  P[2][2] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
3935  P[3][3] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
3936  // velocities
3937  P[4][4] = sq(0.7f);
3938  P[5][5] = P[4][4];
3939  P[6][6] = sq(0.7f);
3940  // positions
3941  P[7][7] = sq(15.0f);
3942  P[8][8] = P[7][7];
3943  P[9][9] = sq(_baroAltNoise);
3944  // delta angle biases
3945  P[10][10] = sq(radians(INIT_GYRO_BIAS_UNCERTAINTY * dtIMUavg));
3946  P[11][11] = P[10][10];
3947  P[12][12] = P[10][10];
3948  // Z delta velocity bias
3949  P[13][13] = sq(INIT_ACCEL_BIAS_UNCERTAINTY * dtIMUavg);
3950  // wind velocities
3951  P[14][14] = 0.0f;
3952  P[15][15] = P[14][14];
3953  // earth magnetic field
3954  P[16][16] = 0.0f;
3955  P[17][17] = P[16][16];
3956  P[18][18] = P[16][16];
3957  // body magnetic field
3958  P[19][19] = 0.0f;
3959  P[20][20] = P[19][19];
3960  P[21][21] = P[19][19];
3961 
3962  // optical flow ground height covariance
3963  Popt = 0.25f;
3964 
3965 }
3966 
3967 // force symmetry on the covariance matrix to prevent ill-conditioning
3968 void NavEKF::ForceSymmetry()
3969 {
3970  for (uint8_t i=1; i<=21; i++)
3971  {
3972  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=i-1; j++)
3973  {
3974  float temp = 0.5f*(P[i][j] + P[j][i]);
3975  P[i][j] = temp;
3976  P[j][i] = temp;
3977  }
3978  }
3979 }
3980 
3981 // copy covariances across from covariance prediction calculation and fix numerical errors
3982 void NavEKF::CopyAndFixCovariances()
3983 {
3984  // copy predicted variances
3985  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=21; i++) {
3986  P[i][i] = nextP[i][i];
3987  }
3988  // copy predicted covariances and force symmetry
3989  for (uint8_t i=1; i<=21; i++) {
3990  for (uint8_t j=0; j<=i-1; j++)
3991  {
3992  P[i][j] = 0.5f*(nextP[i][j] + nextP[j][i]);
3993  P[j][i] = P[i][j];
3994  }
3995  }
3996 }
3997 
3998 // constrain variances (diagonal terms) in the state covariance matrix to prevent ill-conditioning
3999 void NavEKF::ConstrainVariances()
4000 {
4001  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=3; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0f); // quaternions
4002  for (uint8_t i=4; i<=6; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0e3f); // velocities
4003  for (uint8_t i=7; i<=9; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0e6f); // positions
4004  for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,sq(0.175f * dtIMUavg)); // delta angle biases
4005  P[13][13] = constrain_float(P[13][13],0.0f,sq(10.0f * dtIMUavg)); // delta velocity bias
4006  for (uint8_t i=14; i<=15; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0e3f); // earth magnetic field
4007  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=21; i++) P[i][i] = constrain_float(P[i][i],0.0f,1.0f); // body magnetic field
4008 }
4009 
4010 // constrain states to prevent ill-conditioning
4011 void NavEKF::ConstrainStates()
4012 {
4013  // quaternions are limited between +-1
4014  for (uint8_t i=0; i<=3; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-1.0f,1.0f);
4015  // velocity limit 500 m/sec (could set this based on some multiple of max airspeed * EAS2TAS)
4016  for (uint8_t i=4; i<=6; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-5.0e2f,5.0e2f);
4017  // position limit 1000 km - TODO apply circular limit
4018  for (uint8_t i=7; i<=8; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-1.0e6f,1.0e6f);
4019  // height limit covers home alt on everest through to home alt at SL and ballon drop
4020  state.position.z = constrain_float(state.position.z,-4.0e4f,1.0e4f);
4021  // gyro bias limit ~6 deg/sec (this needs to be set based on manufacturers specs)
4022  for (uint8_t i=10; i<=12; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-0.1f*dtIMUavg,0.1f*dtIMUavg);
4023  // Z accel bias limit 1.0 m/s^2 (this needs to be finalised from test data)
4024  states[13] = constrain_float(states[13],-1.0f*dtIMUavg,1.0f*dtIMUavg);
4025  states[22] = constrain_float(states[22],-1.0f*dtIMUavg,1.0f*dtIMUavg);
4026  // wind velocity limit 100 m/s (could be based on some multiple of max airspeed * EAS2TAS) - TODO apply circular limit
4027  for (uint8_t i=14; i<=15; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-100.0f,100.0f);
4028  // earth magnetic field limit
4029  for (uint8_t i=16; i<=18; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-1.0f,1.0f);
4030  // body magnetic field limit
4031  for (uint8_t i=19; i<=21; i++) states[i] = constrain_float(states[i],-0.5f,0.5f);
4032  // constrain the terrain offset state
4033  terrainState = max(terrainState, state.position.z + rngOnGnd);
4034 }

4036 bool NavEKF::readDeltaVelocity(uint8_t ins_index, Vector3f &dVel, float &dVel_dt) {
4037  const AP_InertialSensor &ins = _ahrs->get_ins();
4038 
4039  if (ins_index < ins.get_accel_count()) {
4040  if (ins.get_delta_velocity(ins_index,dVel)) {
4041  dVel_dt = ins.get_delta_velocity_dt(ins_index);
4042  } else {
4043  dVel = ins.get_accel(ins_index) * dtIMUactual;
4044  dVel_dt = dtIMUactual;
4045  }
4046  return true;
4047  }
4048  return false;
4049 }

4051 bool NavEKF::readDeltaAngle(uint8_t ins_index, Vector3f &dAng) {
4052  const AP_InertialSensor &ins = _ahrs->get_ins();
4053 
4054  if (ins_index < ins.get_gyro_count()) {
4055  if (!ins.get_delta_angle(ins_index,dAng)) {
4056  dAng = ins.get_gyro(ins_index) * dtIMUactual;
4057  }
4058  return true;
4059  }
4060  return false;
4061 }
