4063 // update IMU delta angle and delta velocity measurements
4064 void NavEKF::readIMUData()
4065 {
4066  const AP_InertialSensor &ins = _ahrs->get_ins();
4067 
4068  dtIMUavg = 1.0f/ins.get_sample_rate();
4069  dtIMUactual = max(ins.get_delta_time(),1.0e-3f);
4070 
4071  // the imu sample time is used as a common time reference throughout the filter
4072  imuSampleTime_ms = hal.scheduler->millis();
4073 
4074  if (ins.get_accel_health(0) && ins.get_accel_health(1)) {
4075  // dual accel mode
4076  readDeltaVelocity(0, dVelIMU1, dtDelVel1);
4077  readDeltaVelocity(1, dVelIMU2, dtDelVel2);
4078  } else {
4079  // single accel mode - one of the first two accelerometers are unhealthy
4080  // read primary accelerometer into dVelIMU1 and copy to dVelIMU2
4081  readDeltaVelocity(ins.get_primary_accel(), dVelIMU1, dtDelVel1);
4082 
4083  dtDelVel2 = dtDelVel1;
4084  dVelIMU2 = dVelIMU1;
4085  }
4086 
4087  if (ins.get_gyro_health(0) && ins.get_gyro_health(1)) {
4088  // dual gyro mode - average first two gyros
4089  Vector3f dAng;
4090  dAngIMU.zero();
4091  readDeltaAngle(0, dAng);
4092  dAngIMU += dAng;
4093  readDeltaAngle(1, dAng);
4094  dAngIMU += dAng;
4095  dAngIMU *= 0.5f;
4096  } else {
4097  // single gyro mode - one of the first two gyros are unhealthy or don't exist
4098  // just read primary gyro
4099  readDeltaAngle(ins.get_primary_gyro(), dAngIMU);
4100  }
4101 }
4102 
4103 // check for new valid GPS data and update stored measurement if available
4104 void NavEKF::readGpsData()
4105 {
4106  bool goodToAlign = false;
4107  // check for new GPS data
4108  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().last_message_time_ms() != lastFixTime_ms) &&
4109  (_ahrs->get_gps().status() >= AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D))
4110  {
4111  // store fix time from previous read
4112  secondLastFixTime_ms = lastFixTime_ms;
4113 
4114  // get current fix time
4115  lastFixTime_ms = _ahrs->get_gps().last_message_time_ms();
4116 
4117  // set flag that lets other functions know that new GPS data has arrived
4118  newDataGps = true;
4119 
4120  // get state vectors that were stored at the time that is closest to when the the GPS measurement
4121  // time after accounting for measurement delays
4122  RecallStates(statesAtVelTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - constrain_int16(_msecVelDelay, 0, 500)));
4123  RecallStates(statesAtPosTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - constrain_int16(_msecPosDelay, 0, 500)));
4124 
4125  // read the NED velocity from the GPS
4126  velNED = _ahrs->get_gps().velocity();
4127 
4128  // Use the speed accuracy from the GPS if available, otherwise set it to zero.
4129  // Apply a decaying envelope filter with a 5 second time constant to the raw speed accuracy data
4130  float alpha = constrain_float(0.0002f * (lastFixTime_ms - secondLastFixTime_ms),0.0f,1.0f);
4131  gpsSpdAccuracy *= (1.0f - alpha);
4132  float gpsSpdAccRaw;
4133  if (!_ahrs->get_gps().speed_accuracy(gpsSpdAccRaw)) {
4134  gpsSpdAccuracy = 0.0f;
4135  } else {
4136  gpsSpdAccuracy = max(gpsSpdAccuracy,gpsSpdAccRaw);
4137  }
4138 
4139  // check if we have enough GPS satellites and increase the gps noise scaler if we don't
4140  if (_ahrs->get_gps().num_sats() >= 6 && !constPosMode) {
4141  gpsNoiseScaler = 1.0f;
4142  } else if (_ahrs->get_gps().num_sats() == 5 && !constPosMode) {
4143  gpsNoiseScaler = 1.4f;
4144  } else { // <= 4 satellites or in constant position mode
4145  gpsNoiseScaler = 2.0f;
4146  }
4147 
4148  // Check if GPS can output vertical velocity and set GPS fusion mode accordingly
4149  if (!_ahrs->get_gps().have_vertical_velocity()) {
4150  // vertical velocity should not be fused
4151  if (_fusionModeGPS == 0) {
4152  _fusionModeGPS = 1;
4153  }
4154  }
4155 
4156  // Monitor quality of the GPS velocity data for alignment
4157  goodToAlign = calcGpsGoodToAlign();
4158 
4159  // read latitutde and longitude from GPS and convert to local NE position relative to the stored origin
4160  // If we don't have an origin, then set it to the current GPS coordinates
4161  const struct Location &gpsloc = _ahrs->get_gps().location();
4162  if (validOrigin) {
4163  gpsPosNE = location_diff(EKF_origin, gpsloc);
4164  } else if (goodToAlign){
4165  // Set the NE origin to the current GPS position
4166  setOrigin();
4167  // Now we know the location we have an estimate for the magnetic field declination and adjust the earth field accordingly
4168  alignMagStateDeclination();
4169  // Set the height of the NED origin to height of baro height datum relative to GPS height datum'
4170  EKF_origin.alt = gpsloc.alt - hgtMea;
4171  // We are by definition at the origin at the instant of alignment so set NE position to zero
4172  gpsPosNE.zero();
4173  // If the vehicle is in flight (use arm status to determine) and GPS useage isn't explicitly prohibited, we switch to absolute position mode
4174  if (vehicleArmed && _fusionModeGPS != 3) {
4175  constPosMode = false;
4176  PV_AidingMode = AID_ABSOLUTE;
4177  gpsNotAvailable = false;
4178  // Initialise EKF position and velocity states
4179  ResetPosition();
4180  ResetVelocity();
4181  }
4182  }
4183 
4184  // calculate a position offset which is applied to NE position and velocity wherever it is used throughout code to allow GPS position jumps to be accommodated gradually
4185  decayGpsOffset();
4186  }
4187 
4188  // If no previous GPS lock or told not to use it, or EKF origin not set, we declare the GPS unavailable for use
4189  if ((_ahrs->get_gps().status() < AP_GPS::GPS_OK_FIX_3D) || _fusionModeGPS == 3 || !validOrigin) {
4190  gpsNotAvailable = true;
4191  } else {
4192  gpsNotAvailable = false;
4193  }
4194 }
4195 
4196 // check for new altitude measurement data and update stored measurement if available
4197 void NavEKF::readHgtData()
4198 {
4199  // check to see if baro measurement has changed so we know if a new measurement has arrived
4200  if (_baro.get_last_update() != lastHgtMeasTime) {
4201  // Don't use Baro height if operating in optical flow mode as we use range finder instead
4202  if (_fusionModeGPS == 3 && _altSource == 1) {
4203  if ((imuSampleTime_ms - rngValidMeaTime_ms) < 2000) {
4204  // adjust range finder measurement to allow for effect of vehicle tilt and height of sensor
4205  hgtMea = max(rngMea * Tnb_flow.c.z, rngOnGnd);
4206  // get states that were stored at the time closest to the measurement time, taking measurement delay into account
4207  statesAtHgtTime = statesAtFlowTime;
4208  // calculate offset to baro data that enables baro to be used as a backup
4209  // filter offset to reduce effect of baro noise and other transient errors on estimate
4210  baroHgtOffset = 0.1f * (_baro.get_altitude() + state.position.z) + 0.9f * baroHgtOffset;
4211  } else if (vehicleArmed && takeOffDetected) {
4212  // use baro measurement and correct for baro offset - failsafe use only as baro will drift
4213  hgtMea = max(_baro.get_altitude() - baroHgtOffset, rngOnGnd);
4214  // get states that were stored at the time closest to the measurement time, taking measurement delay into account
4215  RecallStates(statesAtHgtTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - msecHgtDelay));
4216  } else {
4217  // If we are on ground and have no range finder reading, assume the nominal on-ground height
4218  hgtMea = rngOnGnd;
4219  // get states that were stored at the time closest to the measurement time, taking measurement delay into account
4220  statesAtHgtTime = state;
4221  // calculate offset to baro data that enables baro to be used as a backup
4222  // filter offset to reduce effect of baro noise and other transient errors on estimate
4223  baroHgtOffset = 0.1f * (_baro.get_altitude() + state.position.z) + 0.9f * baroHgtOffset;
4224  }
4225  } else {
4226  // use baro measurement and correct for baro offset
4227  hgtMea = _baro.get_altitude();
4228  // get states that were stored at the time closest to the measurement time, taking measurement delay into account
4229  RecallStates(statesAtHgtTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - msecHgtDelay));
4230  }
4231 
4232  // filtered baro data used to provide a reference for takeoff
4233  // it is is reset to last height measurement on disarming in performArmingChecks()
4234  if (!getTakeoffExpected()) {
4235  static const float gndHgtFiltTC = 0.5f;
4236  static const float dtBaro = msecHgtAvg*1.0e-3f;
4237  float alpha = constrain_float(dtBaro / (dtBaro+gndHgtFiltTC),0.0f,1.0f);
4238  meaHgtAtTakeOff += (hgtMea-meaHgtAtTakeOff)*alpha;
4239  } else if (vehicleArmed && getTakeoffExpected()) {
4240  // If we are in takeoff mode, the height measurement is limited to be no less than the measurement at start of takeoff
4241  // This prevents negative baro disturbances due to copter downwash corrupting the EKF altitude during initial ascent
4242  hgtMea = max(hgtMea, meaHgtAtTakeOff);
4243  }
4244 
4245  // set flag to let other functions know new data has arrived
4246  newDataHgt = true;
4247  // time stamp used to check for new measurement
4248  lastHgtMeasTime = _baro.get_last_update();
4249  } else {
4250  newDataHgt = false;
4251  }
4252 }
4253 
4254 // check for new magnetometer data and update store measurements if available
4255 void NavEKF::readMagData()
4256 {
4257  if (use_compass() && _ahrs->get_compass()->last_update_usec() != lastMagUpdate) {
4258  // store time of last measurement update
4259  lastMagUpdate = _ahrs->get_compass()->last_update_usec();
4260 
4261  // read compass data and scale to improve numerical conditioning
4262  magData = _ahrs->get_compass()->get_field() * 0.001f;
4263 
4264  // get states stored at time closest to measurement time after allowance for measurement delay
4265  RecallStates(statesAtMagMeasTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - msecMagDelay));
4266 
4267  // let other processes know that new compass data has arrived
4268  newDataMag = true;
4269 
4270  // check if compass offsets have ben changed and adjust EKF bias states to maintain consistent innovations
4271  if (_ahrs->get_compass()->healthy(0)) {
4272  Vector3f nowMagOffsets = _ahrs->get_compass()->get_offsets(0);
4273  bool changeDetected = (!is_equal(nowMagOffsets.x,lastMagOffsets.x) || !is_equal(nowMagOffsets.y,lastMagOffsets.y) || !is_equal(nowMagOffsets.z,lastMagOffsets.z));
4274  // Ignore bias changes before final mag field and yaw initialisation, as there may have been a compass calibration
4275  if (changeDetected && secondMagYawInit) {
4276  state.body_magfield.x += (nowMagOffsets.x - lastMagOffsets.x) * 0.001f;
4277  state.body_magfield.y += (nowMagOffsets.y - lastMagOffsets.y) * 0.001f;
4278  state.body_magfield.z += (nowMagOffsets.z - lastMagOffsets.z) * 0.001f;
4279  }
4280  lastMagOffsets = nowMagOffsets;
4281  }
4282  } else {
4283  newDataMag = false;
4284  }
4285 }
4286 
4287 // check for new airspeed data and update stored measurements if available
4288 void NavEKF::readAirSpdData()
4289 {
4290  // if airspeed reading is valid and is set by the user to be used and has been updated then
4291  // we take a new reading, convert from EAS to TAS and set the flag letting other functions
4292  // know a new measurement is available
4293  const AP_Airspeed *aspeed = _ahrs->get_airspeed();
4294  if (aspeed &&
4295  aspeed->use() &&
4296  aspeed->last_update_ms() != lastAirspeedUpdate) {
4297  VtasMeas = aspeed->get_airspeed() * aspeed->get_EAS2TAS();
4298  lastAirspeedUpdate = aspeed->last_update_ms();
4299  newDataTas = true;
4300  RecallStates(statesAtVtasMeasTime, (imuSampleTime_ms - msecTasDelay));
4301  } else {
4302  newDataTas = false;
4303  }
4304 }

4306 // write the raw optical flow measurements
4307 // this needs to be called externally.
4308 void NavEKF::writeOptFlowMeas(uint8_t &rawFlowQuality, Vector2f &rawFlowRates, Vector2f &rawGyroRates, uint32_t &msecFlowMeas)
4309 {
4310  // The raw measurements need to be optical flow rates in radians/second averaged across the time since the last update
4311  // The PX4Flow sensor outputs flow rates with the following axis and sign conventions:
4312  // A positive X rate is produced by a positive sensor rotation about the X axis
4313  // A positive Y rate is produced by a positive sensor rotation about the Y axis
4314  // This filter uses a different definition of optical flow rates to the sensor with a positive optical flow rate produced by a
4315  // negative rotation about that axis. For example a positive rotation of the flight vehicle about its X (roll) axis would produce a negative X flow rate
4316  flowMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4317  flowQuality = rawFlowQuality;
4318  // recall angular rates averaged across flow observation period allowing for processing, transmission and intersample delays
4319  RecallOmega(omegaAcrossFlowTime, imuSampleTime_ms - flowTimeDeltaAvg_ms - _msecFLowDelay, imuSampleTime_ms - _msecFLowDelay);
4320  // calculate bias errors on flow sensor gyro rates, but protect against spikes in data
4321  flowGyroBias.x = 0.99f * flowGyroBias.x + 0.01f * constrain_float((rawGyroRates.x - omegaAcrossFlowTime.x),-0.1f,0.1f);
4322  flowGyroBias.y = 0.99f * flowGyroBias.y + 0.01f * constrain_float((rawGyroRates.y - omegaAcrossFlowTime.y),-0.1f,0.1f);
4323  // check for takeoff if relying on optical flow and zero measurements until takeoff detected
4324  // if we haven't taken off - constrain position and velocity states
4325  if (_fusionModeGPS == 3) {
4326  detectOptFlowTakeoff();
4327  }
4328  // recall vehicle states at mid sample time for flow observations allowing for delays
4329  RecallStates(statesAtFlowTime, imuSampleTime_ms - _msecFLowDelay - flowTimeDeltaAvg_ms/2);
4330  // calculate rotation matrices at mid sample time for flow observations
4331  statesAtFlowTime.quat.rotation_matrix(Tbn_flow);
4332  Tnb_flow = Tbn_flow.transposed();
4333  // don't use data with a low quality indicator or extreme rates (helps catch corrupt sensor data)
4334  if ((rawFlowQuality > 0) && rawFlowRates.length() < 4.2f && rawGyroRates.length() < 4.2f) {
4335  // correct flow sensor rates for bias
4336  omegaAcrossFlowTime.x = rawGyroRates.x - flowGyroBias.x;
4337  omegaAcrossFlowTime.y = rawGyroRates.y - flowGyroBias.y;
4338  // write uncorrected flow rate measurements that will be used by the focal length scale factor estimator
4339  // note correction for different axis and sign conventions used by the px4flow sensor
4340  flowRadXY[0] = - rawFlowRates.x; // raw (non motion compensated) optical flow angular rate about the X axis (rad/sec)
4341  flowRadXY[1] = - rawFlowRates.y; // raw (non motion compensated) optical flow angular rate about the Y axis (rad/sec)
4342  // write flow rate measurements corrected for body rates
4343  flowRadXYcomp[0] = flowRadXY[0] + omegaAcrossFlowTime.x;
4344  flowRadXYcomp[1] = flowRadXY[1] + omegaAcrossFlowTime.y;
4345  // set flag that will trigger observations
4346  newDataFlow = true;
4347  flowValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4348  } else {
4349  newDataFlow = false;
4350  }
4351 }
4352 
4353 // calculate the NED earth spin vector in rad/sec
4354 void NavEKF::calcEarthRateNED(Vector3f &omega, int32_t latitude) const
4355 {
4356  float lat_rad = radians(latitude*1.0e-7f);
4357  omega.x = earthRate*cosf(lat_rad);
4358  omega.y = 0;
4359  omega.z = -earthRate*sinf(lat_rad);
4360 }

4362 // initialise the earth magnetic field states using declination, suppled roll/pitch
4363 // and magnetometer measurements and return initial attitude quaternion
4364 // if no magnetometer data, do not update magnetic field states and assume zero yaw angle
4365 Quaternion NavEKF::calcQuatAndFieldStates(float roll, float pitch)
4366 {
4367  // declare local variables required to calculate initial orientation and magnetic field
4368  float yaw;
4369  Matrix3f Tbn;
4370  Vector3f initMagNED;
4371  Quaternion initQuat;
4372 
4373  if (use_compass()) {
4374  // calculate rotation matrix from body to NED frame
4375  Tbn.from_euler(roll, pitch, 0.0f);
4376 
4377  // read the magnetometer data
4378  readMagData();
4379 
4380  // rotate the magnetic field into NED axes
4381  initMagNED = Tbn * magData;
4382 
4383  // calculate heading of mag field rel to body heading
4384  float magHeading = atan2f(initMagNED.y, initMagNED.x);
4385 
4386  // get the magnetic declination
4387  float magDecAng = use_compass() ? _ahrs->get_compass()->get_declination() : 0;
4388 
4389  // calculate yaw angle rel to true north
4390  yaw = magDecAng - magHeading;
4391  yawAligned = true;
4392  // calculate initial filter quaternion states using yaw from magnetometer if mag heading healthy
4393  // otherwise use existing heading
4394  if (!badMag) {
4395  initQuat.from_euler(roll, pitch, yaw);
4396  } else {
4397  initQuat = state.quat;
4398  }
4399 
4400  // calculate initial Tbn matrix and rotate Mag measurements into NED
4401  // to set initial NED magnetic field states
4402  initQuat.rotation_matrix(Tbn);
4403  state.earth_magfield = Tbn * magData;
4404 
4405  // align the NE earth magnetic field states with the published declination
4406  alignMagStateDeclination();
4407 
4408  // clear bad magnetometer status
4409  badMag = false;
4410  } else {
4411  initQuat.from_euler(roll, pitch, 0.0f);
4412  yawAligned = false;
4413  }
4414 
4415  // return attitude quaternion
4416  return initQuat;
4417 }
4418 
4419 // this function is used to do a forced alignment of the yaw angle to align with the horizontal velocity
4420 // vector from GPS. It is used to align the yaw angle after launch or takeoff.
4421 void NavEKF::alignYawGPS()
4422 {
4423  if ((sq(velNED[0]) + sq(velNED[1])) > 25.0f) {
4424  float roll;
4425  float pitch;
4426  float oldYaw;
4427  float newYaw;
4428  float yawErr;
4429  // get quaternion from existing filter states and calculate roll, pitch and yaw angles
4430  state.quat.to_euler(roll, pitch, oldYaw);
4431  // calculate course yaw angle
4432  oldYaw = atan2f(state.velocity.y,state.velocity.x);
4433  // calculate yaw angle from GPS velocity
4434  newYaw = atan2f(velNED[1],velNED[0]);
4435  // estimate the yaw error
4436  yawErr = wrap_PI(newYaw - oldYaw);
4437  // If the inertial course angle disagrees with the GPS by more than 45 degrees, we declare the compass as bad
4438  badMag = (fabsf(yawErr) > 0.7854f);
4439  // correct yaw angle using GPS ground course compass failed or if not previously aligned
4440  if (badMag || !yawAligned) {
4441  // correct the yaw angle
4442  newYaw = oldYaw + yawErr;
4443  // calculate new filter quaternion states from Euler angles
4444  state.quat.from_euler(roll, pitch, newYaw);
4445  // the yaw angle is now aligned so update its status
4446  yawAligned = true;
4447  // reset the position and velocity states
4448  ResetPosition();
4449  ResetVelocity();
4450  // reset the covariance for the quaternion, velocity and position states
4451  // zero the matrix entries
4452  zeroRows(P,0,9);
4453  zeroCols(P,0,9);
4454  // quaternions - TODO maths that sets them based on different roll, yaw and pitch uncertainties
4455  P[0][0] = 1.0e-9f;
4456  P[1][1] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
4457  P[2][2] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
4458  P[3][3] = 0.25f*sq(radians(1.0f));
4459  // velocities - we could have a big error coming out of constant position mode due to GPS lag
4460  P[4][4] = 400.0f;
4461  P[5][5] = P[4][4];
4462  P[6][6] = sq(0.7f);
4463  // positions - we could have a big error coming out of constant position mode due to GPS lag
4464  P[7][7] = 400.0f;
4465  P[8][8] = P[7][7];
4466  P[9][9] = sq(5.0f);
4467  }
4468  // Update magnetic field states if the magnetometer is bad
4469  if (badMag) {
4470  Vector3f eulerAngles;
4471  getEulerAngles(eulerAngles);
4472  calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
4473  }
4474  }
4475 }
4476 
4477 // This function is used to do a forced alignment of the wind velocity
4478 // states so that they are set to the reciprocal of the ground speed
4479 // and scaled to STARTUP_WIND_SPEED m/s. This is used when launching a
4480 // fly-forward vehicle without an airspeed sensor on the assumption
4481 // that launch will be into wind and STARTUP_WIND_SPEED is
4482 // representative of typical launch wind
4483 void NavEKF::setWindVelStates()
4484 {
4485  float gndSpd = pythagorous2(state.velocity.x, state.velocity.y);
4486  if (gndSpd > 4.0f) {
4487  // set the wind states to be the reciprocal of the velocity and scale
4488  float scaleFactor = STARTUP_WIND_SPEED / gndSpd;
4489  state.wind_vel.x = - state.velocity.x * scaleFactor;
4490  state.wind_vel.y = - state.velocity.y * scaleFactor;
4491  // reinitialise the wind state covariances
4492  zeroRows(P,14,15);
4493  zeroCols(P,14,15);
4494  P[14][14] = 64.0f;
4495  P[15][15] = P[14][14];
4496  }
4497 }

4500 void NavEKF::getRotationBodyToNED(Matrix3f &mat) const

4502  Vector3f trim = _ahrs->get_trim();
4503  state.quat.rotation_matrix(mat);

4505 }

4686 // decay GPS horizontal position offset to close to zero at a rate of 1 m/s for copters and 5 m/s for planes
4687 // limit radius to a maximum of 50m
4688 void NavEKF::decayGpsOffset()
4689 {
4690  float offsetDecaySpd;
4691  if (assume_zero_sideslip()) {
4692  offsetDecaySpd = 5.0f;
4693  } else {
4694  offsetDecaySpd = 1.0f;
4695  }
4696  float lapsedTime = 0.001f*float(imuSampleTime_ms - lastDecayTime_ms);
4697  lastDecayTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4698  float offsetRadius = pythagorous2(gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.x, gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.y);
4699  // decay radius if larger than offset decay speed multiplied by lapsed time (plus a margin to prevent divide by zero)
4700  if (offsetRadius > (offsetDecaySpd * lapsedTime + 0.1f)) {
4701  // Calculate the GPS velocity offset required. This is necessary to prevent the position measurement being rejected for inconsistency when the radius is being pulled back in.
4702  gpsVelGlitchOffset = -gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE*offsetDecaySpd/offsetRadius;
4703  // calculate scale factor to be applied to both offset components
4704  float scaleFactor = constrain_float((offsetRadius - offsetDecaySpd * lapsedTime), 0.0f, 50.0f) / offsetRadius;
4705  gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.x *= scaleFactor;
4706  gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.y *= scaleFactor;
4707  } else {
4708  gpsVelGlitchOffset.zero();
4709  gpsPosGlitchOffsetNE.zero();
4710  }
4711 }
4712 
4713 /*
4714  should we assume zero sideslip?
4715  */
4716 bool NavEKF::assume_zero_sideslip(void) const
4717 {
4718  // we don't assume zero sideslip for ground vehicles as EKF could
4719  // be quite sensitive to a rapid spin of the ground vehicle if
4720  // traction is lost
4721  return _ahrs->get_fly_forward() && _ahrs->get_vehicle_class() != AHRS_VEHICLE_GROUND;
4722 }

4724 /*
4725 return the filter fault status as a bitmasked integer
4726  0 = quaternions are NaN
4727  1 = velocities are NaN
4728  2 = badly conditioned X magnetometer fusion
4729  3 = badly conditioned Y magnetometer fusion
4730  5 = badly conditioned Z magnetometer fusion
4731  6 = badly conditioned airspeed fusion
4732  7 = badly conditioned synthetic sideslip fusion
4733  7 = filter is not initialised
4734 */
4735 void NavEKF::getFilterFaults(uint8_t &faults) const
4736 {
4737  faults = (state.quat.is_nan()<<0 |
4738  state.velocity.is_nan()<<1 |
4739  faultStatus.bad_xmag<<2 |
4740  faultStatus.bad_ymag<<3 |
4741  faultStatus.bad_zmag<<4 |
4742  faultStatus.bad_airspeed<<5 |
4743  faultStatus.bad_sideslip<<6 |
4744  !statesInitialised<<7);
4745 }

4747 /*
4748 return filter timeout status as a bitmasked integer
4749  0 = position measurement timeout
4750  1 = velocity measurement timeout
4751  2 = height measurement timeout
4752  3 = magnetometer measurement timeout
4753  4 = true airspeed measurement timeout
4754  5 = unassigned
4755  6 = unassigned
4756  7 = unassigned
4757 */
4758 void NavEKF::getFilterTimeouts(uint8_t &timeouts) const
4759 {
4760  timeouts = (posTimeout<<0 |
4761  velTimeout<<1 |
4762  hgtTimeout<<2 |
4763  magTimeout<<3 |
4764  tasTimeout<<4);

4766 
4767 /*
4768 return filter function status as a bitmasked integer
4769  0 = attitude estimate valid
4770  1 = horizontal velocity estimate valid
4771  2 = vertical velocity estimate valid
4772  3 = relative horizontal position estimate valid
4773  4 = absolute horizontal position estimate valid
4774  5 = vertical position estimate valid
4775  6 = terrain height estimate valid
4776  7 = constant position mode
4777 */
4778 void NavEKF::getFilterStatus(nav_filter_status &status) const
4779 {
4780  // init return value
4781  status.value = 0;
4782 
4783  bool doingFlowNav = (PV_AidingMode == AID_RELATIVE) && flowDataValid;
4784  bool doingWindRelNav = !tasTimeout && assume_zero_sideslip();
4785  bool doingNormalGpsNav = !posTimeout && (PV_AidingMode == AID_ABSOLUTE);
4786  bool notDeadReckoning = !constVelMode && !constPosMode;
4787  bool someVertRefData = (!velTimeout && (_fusionModeGPS == 0)) || !hgtTimeout;
4788  bool someHorizRefData = !(velTimeout && posTimeout && tasTimeout) || doingFlowNav;
4789  bool optFlowNavPossible = flowDataValid && (_fusionModeGPS == 3);
4790  bool gpsNavPossible = !gpsNotAvailable && (_fusionModeGPS <= 2);
4791  bool filterHealthy = healthy();
4792 
4793  // set individual flags
4794  status.flags.attitude = !state.quat.is_nan() && filterHealthy; // attitude valid (we need a better check)
4795  status.flags.horiz_vel = someHorizRefData && notDeadReckoning && filterHealthy; // horizontal velocity estimate valid
4796  status.flags.vert_vel = someVertRefData && filterHealthy; // vertical velocity estimate valid
4797  status.flags.horiz_pos_rel = ((doingFlowNav && gndOffsetValid) || doingWindRelNav || doingNormalGpsNav) && notDeadReckoning && filterHealthy; // relative horizontal position estimate valid
4798  status.flags.horiz_pos_abs = !gpsAidingBad && doingNormalGpsNav && notDeadReckoning && filterHealthy; // absolute horizontal position estimate valid
4799  status.flags.vert_pos = !hgtTimeout && filterHealthy; // vertical position estimate valid
4800  status.flags.terrain_alt = gndOffsetValid && filterHealthy; // terrain height estimate valid
4801  status.flags.const_pos_mode = constPosMode && filterHealthy; // constant position mode
4802  status.flags.pred_horiz_pos_rel = (optFlowNavPossible || gpsNavPossible) && filterHealthy; // we should be able to estimate a relative position when we enter flight mode
4803  status.flags.pred_horiz_pos_abs = gpsNavPossible && filterHealthy; // we should be able to estimate an absolute position when we enter flight mode
4804  status.flags.takeoff_detected = takeOffDetected; // takeoff for optical flow navigation has been detected
4805  status.flags.takeoff = expectGndEffectTakeoff; // The EKF has been told to expect takeoff and is in a ground effect mitigation mode
4806  status.flags.touchdown = expectGndEffectTouchdown; // The EKF has been told to detect touchdown and is in a ground effect mitigation mode
4807  status.flags.using_gps = (imuSampleTime_ms - lastPosPassTime) < 4000;
4808 }
4809 
4810 // send an EKF_STATUS message to GCS
4811 void NavEKF::send_status_report(mavlink_channel_t chan)
4812 {
4813  // get filter status
4814  nav_filter_status filt_state;
4815  getFilterStatus(filt_state);
4816 
4817  // prepare flags
4818  uint16_t flags = 0;
4819  if (filt_state.flags.attitude) { flags |= EKF_ATTITUDE; }
4820  if (filt_state.flags.horiz_vel) { flags |= EKF_VELOCITY_HORIZ; }
4821  if (filt_state.flags.vert_vel) { flags |= EKF_VELOCITY_VERT; }
4822  if (filt_state.flags.horiz_pos_rel) { flags |= EKF_POS_HORIZ_REL; }
4823  if (filt_state.flags.horiz_pos_abs) { flags |= EKF_POS_HORIZ_ABS; }
4824  if (filt_state.flags.vert_pos) { flags |= EKF_POS_VERT_ABS; }
4825  if (filt_state.flags.terrain_alt) { flags |= EKF_POS_VERT_AGL; }
4826  if (filt_state.flags.const_pos_mode) { flags |= EKF_CONST_POS_MODE; }
4827  if (filt_state.flags.pred_horiz_pos_rel) { flags |= EKF_PRED_POS_HORIZ_REL; }
4828  if (filt_state.flags.pred_horiz_pos_abs) { flags |= EKF_PRED_POS_HORIZ_ABS; }
4829 
4830  // get variances
4831  float velVar, posVar, hgtVar, tasVar;
4832  Vector3f magVar;
4833  Vector2f offset;
4834  getVariances(velVar, posVar, hgtVar, magVar, tasVar, offset);
4835 
4836  // send message
4837  mavlink_msg_ekf_status_report_send(chan, flags, velVar, posVar, hgtVar, magVar.length(), tasVar);
4838 
4839 }

4841 // Check arm status and perform required checks and mode changes
4842 void NavEKF::performArmingChecks()
4843 {
4844  // determine vehicle arm status and don't allow filter to arm until it has been running for long enough to stabilise
4845  prevVehicleArmed = vehicleArmed;
4846  vehicleArmed = (getVehicleArmStatus() && (imuSampleTime_ms - ekfStartTime_ms) > 1000);
4847 
4848  // check to see if arm status has changed and reset states if it has
4849  if (vehicleArmed != prevVehicleArmed) {
4850  // only reset the magnetic field and heading on the first arm. This prevents in-flight learning being forgotten for vehicles that do multiple short flights and disarm in-between.
4851  if (vehicleArmed && !firstArmComplete) {
4852  firstArmComplete = true;
4853  Vector3f eulerAngles;
4854  getEulerAngles(eulerAngles);
4855  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
4856  }
4857  // store vertical position at arming to use as a reference for ground relative cehcks
4858  if (vehicleArmed) {
4859  posDownAtArming = state.position.z;
4860  }
4861  // zero stored velocities used to do dead-reckoning
4862  heldVelNE.zero();
4863  // reset the flag that indicates takeoff for use by optical flow navigation
4864  takeOffDetected = false;
4865  // set various useage modes based on the condition at arming. These are then held until the vehicle is disarmed.
4866  if (!vehicleArmed) {
4867  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE; // When dis-armed, we only estimate orientation & height using the constant position mode
4868  posTimeout = true;
4869  velTimeout = true;
4870  constPosMode = true;
4871  constVelMode = false; // always clear constant velocity mode if constant position mode is active
4872  lastConstVelMode = false;
4873  // store the current position to be used to keep reporting the last known position when disarmed
4874  lastKnownPositionNE.x = state.position.x;
4875  lastKnownPositionNE.y = state.position.y;
4876  // initialise filtered altitude used to provide a takeoff reference to current baro on disarm
4877  // this reduces the time required for the filter to settle before the estimate can be used
4878  meaHgtAtTakeOff = hgtMea;
4879  // reset the vertical position state to faster recover from baro errors experienced during touchdown
4880  state.position.z = -hgtMea;
4881  } else if (_fusionModeGPS == 3) { // arming when GPS useage has been prohibited
4882  if (optFlowDataPresent()) {
4883  PV_AidingMode = AID_RELATIVE; // we have optical flow data and can estimate all vehicle states
4884  posTimeout = true;
4885  velTimeout = true;
4886  constPosMode = false;
4887  constVelMode = false;
4888  } else {
4889  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE; // we don't have optical flow data and will only be able to estimate orientation and height
4890  posTimeout = true;
4891  velTimeout = true;
4892  constPosMode = true;
4893  constVelMode = false; // always clear constant velocity mode if constant position mode is active
4894  }
4895  // Reset the last valid flow measurement time
4896  flowValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4897  // Reset the last valid flow fusion time
4898  prevFlowFuseTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4899  // this avoids issues casued by the time delay associated with arming that can trigger short timeouts
4900  rngValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4901  // store the range finder measurement which will be used as a reference to detect when we have taken off
4902  rangeAtArming = rngMea;
4903  // set the time at which we arm to assist with takeoff detection
4904  timeAtArming_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4905  } else { // arming when GPS useage is allowed
4906  if (gpsNotAvailable) {
4907  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE; // we don't have have GPS data and will only be able to estimate orientation and height
4908  posTimeout = true;
4909  velTimeout = true;
4910  constPosMode = true;
4911  constVelMode = false; // always clear constant velocity mode if constant position mode is active
4912  } else {
4913  PV_AidingMode = AID_ABSOLUTE; // we have GPS data and can estimate all vehicle states
4914  posTimeout = false;
4915  velTimeout = false;
4916  constPosMode = false;
4917  constVelMode = false;
4918  // we need to reset the GPS timers to prevent GPS timeout logic being invoked on entry into GPS aiding
4919  // this is becasue the EKF can be interrupted for an arbitrary amount of time during vehicle arming checks
4920  lastFixTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4921  secondLastFixTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
4922  // reset the last valid position fix time to prevent unwanted activation of GPS glitch logic
4923  lastPosPassTime = imuSampleTime_ms;
4924  // reset the fail time to prevent premature reporting of loss of position accruacy
4925  lastPosFailTime = 0;
4926  }
4927  }
4928  if (vehicleArmed) {
4929  // Reset filter position to GPS when transitioning into flight mode
4930  // We need to do this becasue the vehicle may have moved since the EKF origin was set
4931  ResetPosition();
4932  StoreStatesReset();
4933  } else {
4934  // Reset all position and velocity states when transitioning out of flight mode
4935  // We need to do this becasue we are going into a mode that assumes zero position and velocity
4936  ResetVelocity();
4937  ResetPosition();
4938  StoreStatesReset();
4939  }
4940 
4941  } else if (vehicleArmed && !firstMagYawInit && (state.position.z - posDownAtArming) < -1.5f && !assume_zero_sideslip()) {
4942  // Do the first in-air yaw and earth mag field initialisation when the vehicle has gained 1.5m of altitude after arming if it is a non-fly forward vehicle (vertical takeoff)
4943  // This is done to prevent magnetic field distoration from steel roofs and adjacent structures causing bad earth field and initial yaw values
4944  Vector3f eulerAngles;
4945  getEulerAngles(eulerAngles);
4946  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
4947  firstMagYawInit = true;
4948  } else if (vehicleArmed && !secondMagYawInit && (state.position.z - posDownAtArming) < -5.0f && !assume_zero_sideslip()) {
4949  // Do the second and final yaw and earth mag field initialisation when the vehicle has gained 5.0m of altitude after arming if it is a non-fly forward vehicle (vertical takeoff)
4950  // This second and final correction is needed for flight from large metal structures where the magnetic field distortion can extend up to 5m
4951  Vector3f eulerAngles;
4952  getEulerAngles(eulerAngles);
4953  state.quat = calcQuatAndFieldStates(eulerAngles.x, eulerAngles.y);
4954  secondMagYawInit = true;
4955  }
4956 
4957  // Always turn aiding off when the vehicle is disarmed
4958  if (!vehicleArmed) {
4959  PV_AidingMode = AID_NONE;
4960  posTimeout = true;
4961  velTimeout = true;
4962  // set constant position mode if aiding is inhibited
4963  constPosMode = true;
4964  constVelMode = false; // always clear constant velocity mode if constant position mode is active
4965  lastConstVelMode = false;
4966  }
4967 
4968 }

5034 // Monitor GPS data to see if quality is good enough to initialise the EKF
5035 // Monitor magnetometer innovations to to see if the heading is good enough to use GPS
5036 // Return true if all criteria pass for 10 seconds
5037 bool NavEKF::calcGpsGoodToAlign(void)
5038 {
5039  // calculate absolute difference between GPS vert vel and inertial vert vel
5040  float velDiffAbs;
5041  if (_ahrs->get_gps().have_vertical_velocity()) {
5042  velDiffAbs = fabsf(velNED.z - state.velocity.z);
5043  } else {
5044  velDiffAbs = 0.0f;
5045  }
5046  // fail if velocity difference or reported speed accuracy greater than threshold
5047  bool gpsVelFail = (velDiffAbs > 1.0f) || (gpsSpdAccuracy > 1.0f);
5048  // fail if not enough sats
5049  bool numSatsFail = _ahrs->get_gps().num_sats() < 6;
5050  // fail if horiziontal position accuracy not sufficient
5051  float hAcc = 0.0f;
5052  bool hAccFail;
5053  if (_ahrs->get_gps().horizontal_accuracy(hAcc)) {
5054  hAccFail = hAcc > 5.0f;
5055  } else {
5056  hAccFail = false;
5057  }
5058  // fail if magnetometer innovations are outside limits indicating bad yaw
5059  // with bad yaw we are unable to use GPS
5060  bool yawFail;
5061  if (magTestRatio.x > 1.0f || magTestRatio.y > 1.0f) {
5062  yawFail = true;
5063  } else {
5064  yawFail = false;
5065  }
5066  // record time of fail
5067  // assume fail first time called
5068  if (gpsVelFail || numSatsFail || hAccFail || yawFail || lastGpsVelFail_ms == 0) {
5069  lastGpsVelFail_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5070  }
5071  // DEBUG PRINT
5072  //hal.console->printf("velDiff = %5.2f, nSats = %i, hAcc = %5.2f, sAcc = %5.2f, delTime = %i\n", velDiffAbs, _ahrs->get_gps().num_sats(), hAcc, gpsSpdAccuracy, imuSampleTime_ms - lastGpsVelFail_ms);
5073  // continuous period without fail required to return healthy
5074  if (imuSampleTime_ms - lastGpsVelFail_ms > 10000) {
5075  return true;
5076  } else {
5077  return false;
5078  }
5079 }
5080 
5081 // Read the range finder and take new measurements if available
5082 // Read at 20Hz and apply a median filter
5083 void NavEKF::readRangeFinder(void)
5084 {
5085  static float storedRngMeas[3];
5086  static uint32_t storedRngMeasTime_ms[3];
5087  static uint32_t lastRngMeasTime_ms = 0;
5088  static uint8_t rngMeasIndex = 0;
5089  uint8_t midIndex;
5090  uint8_t maxIndex;
5091  uint8_t minIndex;
5092  // get theoretical correct range when the vehicle is on the ground
5093  rngOnGnd = _rng.ground_clearance_cm() * 0.01f;
5094  if (_rng.status() == RangeFinder::RangeFinder_Good && (imuSampleTime_ms - lastRngMeasTime_ms) > 50) {
5095  // store samples and sample time into a ring buffer
5096  rngMeasIndex ++;
5097  if (rngMeasIndex > 2) {
5098  rngMeasIndex = 0;
5099  }
5100  storedRngMeasTime_ms[rngMeasIndex] = imuSampleTime_ms;
5101  storedRngMeas[rngMeasIndex] = _rng.distance_cm() * 0.01f;
5102  // check for three fresh samples and take median
5103  bool sampleFresh[3];
5104  for (uint8_t index = 0; index <= 2; index++) {
5105  sampleFresh[index] = (imuSampleTime_ms - storedRngMeasTime_ms[index]) < 500;
5106  }
5107  if (sampleFresh[0] && sampleFresh[1] && sampleFresh[2]) {
5108  if (storedRngMeas[0] > storedRngMeas[1]) {
5109  minIndex = 1;
5110  maxIndex = 0;
5111  } else {
5112  maxIndex = 0;
5113  minIndex = 1;
5114  }
5115  if (storedRngMeas[2] > storedRngMeas[maxIndex]) {
5116  midIndex = maxIndex;
5117  } else if (storedRngMeas[2] < storedRngMeas[minIndex]) {
5118  midIndex = minIndex;
5119  } else {
5120  midIndex = 2;
5121  }
5122  rngMea = max(storedRngMeas[midIndex],rngOnGnd);
5123  newDataRng = true;
5124  rngValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5125  // recall vehicle states at mid sample time for range finder
5126  RecallStates(statesAtRngTime, storedRngMeasTime_ms[midIndex] - 25);
5127  } else if (!vehicleArmed) {
5128  // if not armed and no return, we assume on ground range
5129  rngMea = rngOnGnd;
5130  newDataRng = true;
5131  rngValidMeaTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5132  // assume synthetic measurement is at current time (no delay)
5133  statesAtRngTime = state;
5134  } else {
5135  newDataRng = false;
5136  }
5137  lastRngMeasTime_ms = imuSampleTime_ms;
5138  }
5139 }
5140 
5141 // Detect takeoff for optical flow navigation
5142 void NavEKF::detectOptFlowTakeoff(void)
5143 {
5144  if (vehicleArmed && !takeOffDetected && (imuSampleTime_ms - timeAtArming_ms) > 1000) {
5145  const AP_InertialSensor &ins = _ahrs->get_ins();
5146  Vector3f angRateVec;
5147  Vector3f gyroBias;
5148  getGyroBias(gyroBias);
5149  bool dual_ins = ins.get_gyro_health(0) && ins.get_gyro_health(1);
5150  if (dual_ins) {
5151  angRateVec = (ins.get_gyro(0) + ins.get_gyro(1)) * 0.5f - gyroBias;
5152  } else {
5153  angRateVec = ins.get_gyro() - gyroBias;
5154  }
5155 
5156  takeOffDetected = (takeOffDetected || (angRateVec.length() > 0.1f) || (rngMea > (rangeAtArming + 0.1f)));
5157  }
5158 }

5160 // provides the height limit to be observed by the control loops
5161 // returns false if no height limiting is required
5162 // this is needed to ensure the vehicle does not fly too high when using optical flow navigation
5163 bool NavEKF::getHeightControlLimit(float &height) const
5164 {
5165  // only ask for limiting if we are doing optical flow navigation
5166  if (_fusionModeGPS == 3) {
5167  // If are doing optical flow nav, ensure the height above ground is within range finder limits after accounting for vehicle tilt and control errors
5168  height = max(float(_rng.max_distance_cm()) * 0.007f - 1.0f, 1.0f);
5169  return true;
5170  } else {
5171  return false;
5172  }
5173 }

5189 // align the NE earth magnetic field states with the published declination
5190 void NavEKF::alignMagStateDeclination()
5191 {
5192  // get the magnetic declination
5193  float magDecAng = use_compass() ? _ahrs->get_compass()->get_declination() : 0;
5194 
5195  // rotate the NE values so that the declination matches the published value
5196  Vector3f initMagNED = state.earth_magfield;
5197  float magLengthNE = pythagorous2(initMagNED.x,initMagNED.y);
5198  state.earth_magfield.x = magLengthNE * cosf(magDecAng);
5199  state.earth_magfield.y = magLengthNE * sinf(magDecAng);
5200 }
